WEBVTT

00:57.480 --> 00:59.596
Lobbying is about foresight.

01:01.720 --> 01:04.075
About anticipating
your opponent's moves

01:05.120 --> 01:07.190
and devising countermeasures.

01:10.280 --> 01:13.636
The winner plots one step
ahead of the opposition,

01:15.400 --> 01:16.879
and plays her trump card

01:18.480 --> 01:20.436
just after they play theirs.

01:22.840 --> 01:24.136
You better
not be saying that

01:24.160 --> 01:25.309
when you're in there.

01:26.040 --> 01:27.871
It's about making sure
you surprise them,

01:30.280 --> 01:32.430
and they don't surprise you.

01:41.600 --> 01:42.874
I'm gonna ask you again.

01:43.240 --> 01:44.296
Miss Sloane, could you please

01:44.320 --> 01:45.719
describe the nature
of your work?

01:51.720 --> 01:53.096
On the advice of counsel,

01:53.120 --> 01:54.896
I respectfully decline
to answer your question,

01:54.920 --> 01:56.751
based on my rights
under the Fifth Amendment

01:56.840 --> 01:58.160
to the United States
Constitution.

02:00.360 --> 02:01.588
Those words,

02:02.760 --> 02:04.576
when you're not taking the
oath or confirming details,

02:04.600 --> 02:06.680
those words, in that order,
are all you're gonna say.

02:11.720 --> 02:13.995
"On average, would you say
you bribed public officials

02:14.080 --> 02:15.360
"more or less
than once a month?"

02:15.920 --> 02:18.718
Upon the advice of counsel...
Can I deviate slightly?

02:18.800 --> 02:20.400
"On the advice of counsel"?
On the advice

02:20.760 --> 02:21.816
- "of my attorney"?
- You do not...

02:21.840 --> 02:23.910
Okay, okay, I understand
that last one's

02:24.000 --> 02:25.194
too adventurous for you.

02:28.480 --> 02:30.080
This would be
a whole lot easier

02:30.240 --> 02:31.639
if I could just shout "Fifth."

02:32.200 --> 02:33.349
They want you behind bars.

02:34.640 --> 02:35.675
You make one statement,

02:35.800 --> 02:37.313
you correct one
nefarious allegation,

02:37.400 --> 02:38.879
that's it.

02:38.960 --> 02:40.240
You waive your right
to the Fifth

02:40.280 --> 02:41.920
and you're compelled
to answer everything.

02:43.200 --> 02:44.376
They're taking you
to the woodshed

02:44.400 --> 02:45.600
in front of
the national press.

02:46.280 --> 02:47.838
They're gonna rile you so bad

02:48.080 --> 02:50.116
they'd make Gandhi wanna
cut their tongues out.

02:52.960 --> 02:54.656
" Did you arrange for
benefits such as travel,

02:54.680 --> 02:55.749
"luxury accommodations,

02:55.840 --> 02:57.176
"and sports tickets
to be furnished

02:57.200 --> 02:58.315
"to members of Congress

02:58.400 --> 02:59.753
"at the behest
of your clients?"

03:03.280 --> 03:04.976
" Did you arrange for benefits
such as travel,

03:05.000 --> 03:07.275
"luxury accommodations,
and sports tickets to..."

03:07.360 --> 03:08.560
Daniel. When I take the stand,

03:08.640 --> 03:10.153
you'll see nothing
but a granite wall.

03:12.240 --> 03:13.389
Good.

03:33.400 --> 03:34.674
Miss Sloane!

03:38.840 --> 03:40.910
Nothing to say, guys,
thank you.

03:54.120 --> 03:55.758
Miss Sloane, Miss Sloane!

04:00.840 --> 04:02.193
This is tight.

04:03.040 --> 04:05.200
You'd think they would choose
a more appropriate venue.

04:05.800 --> 04:07.916
Well, turns out the Nationals
had a home game.

04:15.840 --> 04:16.955
Good morning.

04:17.040 --> 04:19.235
I am Senator Ronald Sperling,

04:19.360 --> 04:21.635
Chair of this Hearing.
Miss Sloane...

04:28.200 --> 04:29.633
Please raise your right hand.

04:31.360 --> 04:33.476
Do you solemnly swear
that you will tell the truth,

04:33.560 --> 04:35.176
the whole truth,
and nothing but the truth,

04:35.200 --> 04:37.475
under pains and penalties
of perjury?

04:37.560 --> 04:39.118
- I do.
- Please, sit.

04:40.920 --> 04:42.990
Will the witness please
state her full name

04:43.080 --> 04:44.308
for the record?

04:44.400 --> 04:45.799
Madeline Elizabeth Sloane.

04:45.880 --> 04:47.029
Louder, please.

04:48.800 --> 04:50.677
Madeline Elizabeth Sloane.

04:50.880 --> 04:52.496
And could
the witness please confirm

04:52.520 --> 04:54.954
that these details
are accurate...

04:55.280 --> 04:56.474
Uh...

04:56.560 --> 05:00.348
Date of birth, July 26, 1976,
address...

05:00.920 --> 05:02.069
Suite 504, Watergate South,

05:02.160 --> 05:04.390
700 New Hampshire Avenue
North West, Washington D.C.?

05:05.040 --> 05:06.075
Correct.

05:06.200 --> 05:11.069
You were employed by Cole,
Kravitz and Waterman LLP

05:11.320 --> 05:13.629
for a 10-year period
between 2006 and 2016,

05:13.720 --> 05:14.776
before moving on earlier...

05:14.800 --> 05:15.800
Eleven year period.

05:17.400 --> 05:18.435
Excuse me?

05:18.520 --> 05:21.512
There are 11 years
between 2006 and 2016.

05:26.480 --> 05:27.720
What was the nature
of your work

05:27.760 --> 05:29.990
with Cole, Kravitz
and Waterman LLP?

05:34.560 --> 05:35.675
Upon the advice of counsel,

05:35.760 --> 05:37.830
I must respectfully decline
to answer your question,

05:38.640 --> 05:40.360
based on my rights
under the Fifth Amendment

05:40.400 --> 05:42.072
to the United States
Constitution.

05:42.680 --> 05:45.558
Did you,
October 12th of last year,

05:45.640 --> 05:47.631
accept as a client
the government

05:47.720 --> 05:49.950
of the Asian Republic
of Indonesia,

05:50.040 --> 05:51.758
for the purpose of
campaigning against

05:51.840 --> 05:54.229
the levy of additional
Federal duties

05:54.320 --> 05:57.596
on the importation of palm oil
into the United States?

05:59.520 --> 06:00.748
Upon the advice of counsel,

06:00.880 --> 06:03.235
I must respectfully decline
to answer your question,

06:03.320 --> 06:05.231
based on my rights
under the Fifth Amendment

06:05.480 --> 06:07.516
to the United States
Constitution.

06:12.000 --> 06:13.877
Today is a landmark day,
you know why?

06:13.960 --> 06:15.029
Because I'm free.

06:15.120 --> 06:16.348
Name one thing
you can do today

06:16.480 --> 06:17.696
that you couldn't have
done yesterday.

06:17.720 --> 06:18.720
Quit my job.

06:18.800 --> 06:19.896
You could've
done that yesterday,

06:19.920 --> 06:20.976
but it would've been stupid.

06:21.000 --> 06:22.896
- I can quit today and...
- It'd still be stupid.

06:22.920 --> 06:24.069
You clear your college debt

06:24.160 --> 06:25.878
and celebrate by
enrolling in post-grad?

06:27.120 --> 06:28.792
Academia's more my scene.

06:28.920 --> 06:30.256
You didn't follow me
into the crapper

06:30.280 --> 06:32.271
to gloat about freedom, Jane.

06:32.360 --> 06:34.749
Talk to me about
the Nutella Tax.

06:34.840 --> 06:36.751
Uh, we're really calling it
the "Nutella Tax"?

06:36.840 --> 06:38.592
Palm oil is a key ingredient
in Nutella.

06:39.080 --> 06:40.832
If the Federal Government
taxes it at 300%,

06:41.360 --> 06:43.476
it'll cost more for us
to gorge ourselves on it.

06:44.120 --> 06:46.031
Isn't palm oil in
pretty much everything?

06:46.680 --> 06:48.120
We could have called it
the Soap Tax,

06:48.160 --> 06:49.376
but the public cares
more about Nutella

06:49.400 --> 06:50.400
than they do soap.

06:51.120 --> 06:52.400
Anyway, we get
four more senators

06:52.440 --> 06:53.600
to come out against the bill,

06:53.640 --> 06:55.080
we can lean on Jacobs
to withdraw it.

06:56.200 --> 06:57.349
What are you gonna do?

06:58.120 --> 07:00.360
Tell the Indonesians they're
going to host Senator Jacobs

07:00.440 --> 07:02.396
on a field trip to
one of their plantations.

07:02.480 --> 07:04.277
You never washed your hands.

07:06.080 --> 07:09.436
He'll take the wife and kids
on a tropical vacation.

07:09.520 --> 07:12.034
Come back hailing
their conservation efforts.

07:12.720 --> 07:14.551
His bill dies a quiet death.

07:14.640 --> 07:16.296
If the Indonesian
government pays for it,

07:16.320 --> 07:17.389
it's illegal.

07:17.480 --> 07:19.755
If they use a non-profit c3
to sponsor the travel,

07:19.840 --> 07:21.239
it's perfectly legal.

07:21.320 --> 07:23.200
As long as the trip
is for educational purposes.

07:23.400 --> 07:25.675
But, the Indonesian government
is still paying for it.

07:25.760 --> 07:28.149
See, this is why I'm thinking
about post-grad.

07:28.240 --> 07:30.800
Jane, we go to school to
prepare us for the real world.

07:30.880 --> 07:32.359
I'm not sure
I like the real world.

07:32.440 --> 07:34.016
So you want to bury
your head in Socrates?

07:34.040 --> 07:36.873
You know that Socrates
never actually wrote anything.

07:37.800 --> 07:38.915
That's beside the point.

07:39.000 --> 07:40.513
If you don't like it,
you change it.

07:40.600 --> 07:42.636
- That's why you're here.
- Miss Sloane!

07:42.720 --> 07:44.456
They're ready for you
in the conference room.

07:44.480 --> 07:46.456
Hey, Spencer, did you know
that Americans care more

07:46.480 --> 07:48.596
about Nutella than
they do about soap?

07:50.160 --> 07:51.388
Uh, okay.

07:51.920 --> 07:53.035
See that?

07:53.480 --> 07:54.754
No reaction.

07:55.240 --> 07:56.776
Okay, guys, we
gotta be quick this morning,

07:56.800 --> 07:58.153
I've got a meeting to get to.

07:58.240 --> 08:00.151
How many are they
expecting at the IMF rally?

08:00.240 --> 08:01.434
Between 500 and 1,000.

08:01.520 --> 08:03.351
There's a margin of 100%?

08:03.440 --> 08:05.416
Does that technically mean
that nobody might show up?

08:05.440 --> 08:07.874
Five hundred's the minimum,
the rest depends on weather.

08:07.960 --> 08:09.871
Seems more people hate
banks when the sun's out.

08:09.960 --> 08:11.576
- What's the weather forecast?
- Liz?

08:11.600 --> 08:12.736
Time we sold Jacobs
on Indonesia.

08:12.760 --> 08:13.829
I know.

08:13.920 --> 08:16.434
- When Henry falls we've got...
- Critical mass, I'm aware.

08:16.520 --> 08:18.795
Get a non-profit
to sponsor a vacation.

08:18.880 --> 08:20.871
They give him face
and he'll pull it.

08:20.960 --> 08:23.030
Did you just come from
the ladies' room?

08:23.280 --> 08:25.016
Uh, I have no idea
what you're talking about.

08:25.040 --> 08:26.976
We're talking about
numbers at the IMF rally.

08:27.000 --> 08:29.036
All right, Alex,
put Metro Talent on notice,

08:29.120 --> 08:31.076
- we may need reinforcements.
- I'm on it.

08:31.160 --> 08:32.336
We're really gonna
use movie extras?

08:32.360 --> 08:33.776
The guy shouting about
corporate greed

08:33.800 --> 08:35.438
becomes a lot less
credible standing next

08:35.520 --> 08:37.033
to a hobo from central casting,

08:37.160 --> 08:39.515
with a banner that reads,
"Abolish money."

08:39.600 --> 08:40.749
"Shit is fucked up

08:40.840 --> 08:42.193
"and bullshit."

08:42.560 --> 08:44.994
Best banner at Occupy.
Tell me that was one of ours.

08:45.080 --> 08:47.719
Oh, no, that was creative
way beyond my capabilities.

08:47.800 --> 08:50.792
- Franklin! Shmallow Cakes?
- Uh, yeah!

08:50.880 --> 08:52.416
Does sales tax apply
to cakes and cookies,

08:52.440 --> 08:53.440
or only to one of those?

08:54.640 --> 08:56.471
I don't know.

09:00.920 --> 09:01.955
You don't know?

09:03.520 --> 09:04.576
All right, everybody, listen up!

09:04.600 --> 09:05.776
I'm going to tell you a story.

09:05.800 --> 09:06.835
Please, no.

09:06.920 --> 09:08.216
A priest is
giving a young nun

09:08.240 --> 09:09.639
a lift home from
church one day,

09:09.720 --> 09:11.312
and as he's shifting gears,

09:11.400 --> 09:13.960
he rests his hand
on the nun's knee.

09:14.480 --> 09:15.736
This is offensive
and inappropriate.

09:15.760 --> 09:17.296
The young nun looks up
at the priest and says,

09:17.320 --> 09:20.118
"Father, remember Luke 14:10."

09:20.960 --> 09:22.837
The priest withdraws his hand,
embarrassed.

09:23.120 --> 09:24.792
Next time
they stop at a light,

09:25.040 --> 09:27.554
he places his hand a little
higher up on her thigh,

09:27.640 --> 09:31.110
again the nun says,
"Remember Luke 14:10, Father."

09:31.680 --> 09:33.079
The priest apologizes.

09:33.160 --> 09:35.435
"The flesh is weak," he says.

09:35.640 --> 09:37.256
So he drops her off,
and when he gets home,

09:37.280 --> 09:40.909
he reaches for his bible
and he flips to Luke 14:10.

09:41.000 --> 09:42.558
Anyone know what it says? Hmm?

09:44.200 --> 09:45.553
What does it say, Pat?

09:45.920 --> 09:49.276
"Friend, come up higher,
then shalt thou have glory!"

09:49.400 --> 09:51.436
Know your subject, people!

09:52.400 --> 09:53.833
Failure to do so may result

09:53.920 --> 09:55.478
in the loss of
a golden opportunity.

09:55.720 --> 09:57.278
When I see you this afternoon,

09:57.360 --> 09:58.416
you'd better be
ready to recite

09:58.440 --> 10:00.590
that tax code in Esperanto.

10:04.120 --> 10:07.669
I'm... I'm told I should
offer her my hand, huh?

10:08.720 --> 10:10.278
How do you mean?

10:10.960 --> 10:13.997
Well, when we meet,
I'm told that

10:14.080 --> 10:17.072
she doesn't care for
all that kissy-kissy stuff

10:17.160 --> 10:19.469
that most women do these days.

10:19.560 --> 10:21.915
You two
have never met?

10:22.000 --> 10:24.434
Well, we've been to several
of the same functions, yeah,

10:24.560 --> 10:26.039
but we've never
been introduced.

10:26.120 --> 10:28.634
In a town this small,
how does that happen?

10:30.440 --> 10:32.715
So, should I
offer my hand?

10:32.800 --> 10:34.120
I wouldn't
worry about it.

10:35.760 --> 10:37.796
- Liz?
- Good morning!

10:37.960 --> 10:39.234
Bill Sandford.

10:39.320 --> 10:40.753
I'm amazed
it's taken this long.

10:40.960 --> 10:43.110
Well, you know, I wanted
to introduce myself

10:43.200 --> 10:44.400
at the Free Enterprise Dinner,

10:44.520 --> 10:47.114
but you were the first one
out the door.

10:47.200 --> 10:48.997
Minor crisis on the Hill.

10:49.600 --> 10:50.749
Well, a lesser commander

10:50.840 --> 10:52.353
would've left that
to a soldier,

10:52.440 --> 10:54.192
which is the reason I'm here.

10:54.280 --> 10:56.236
Why exactly are you here?

10:56.320 --> 10:58.151
Killing bills
like Heaton-Harris,

10:58.240 --> 10:59.798
that's food and drink
to you guys.

10:59.880 --> 11:02.110
- So you've read it?
- No, but I know what it is.

11:02.200 --> 11:03.758
It's a bipartisan gun bill

11:03.840 --> 11:05.353
requiring universal
background checks.

11:05.800 --> 11:08.792
On all sales of firearms.

11:08.880 --> 11:10.199
Now, come on.

11:10.280 --> 11:13.511
A father and his son,
lifelong friends.

11:13.600 --> 11:16.319
It just means longer delays.

11:16.400 --> 11:18.311
It's some kind of
Big Brother type criminal

11:18.400 --> 11:20.231
and mental health database.

11:20.320 --> 11:23.039
An unconstitutional fetter
on the Second Amendment

11:23.160 --> 11:24.991
which, as you said,

11:26.400 --> 11:27.753
we will eat for breakfast.

11:30.000 --> 11:32.355
Mr. Sandford, I deal
primarily in taxation

11:32.680 --> 11:33.976
and Federal Government
interference

11:34.000 --> 11:35.080
in free enterprise. This...

11:35.120 --> 11:36.678
I'm aware, I am aware.

11:37.360 --> 11:38.360
But I'll tell you,

11:38.440 --> 11:40.431
the reputation you have
garnered for yourself,

11:40.520 --> 11:42.909
we were just looking for
an excuse to engage you.

11:43.960 --> 11:45.313
Okay. Let's have it.

11:51.360 --> 11:52.554
Women.

11:53.520 --> 11:55.033
Our polling data is telling us

11:55.120 --> 11:57.156
that we're not connecting
with the female voter.

11:58.960 --> 12:01.269
So, we want to change
the narrative.

12:01.360 --> 12:04.511
From mothers losing
their kids to guns,

12:04.600 --> 12:07.239
to mothers protecting
their kids with guns.

12:08.360 --> 12:10.794
From a battered wife
threatened by a bullet,

12:10.880 --> 12:14.475
to fending off her
violent husband with a.38.

12:15.120 --> 12:17.634
Guns as tools
of female empowerment.

12:18.840 --> 12:20.637
What's the saying?
God created humans...

12:20.760 --> 12:23.513
Samuel Colt made them equal.

12:26.200 --> 12:29.909
Now, Liz, imagine
a new organization,

12:31.000 --> 12:33.468
pitched at women
who are deterred

12:34.480 --> 12:37.233
by the strong rhetoric of the
Second Amendment groups,

12:37.360 --> 12:40.193
and by our association
with the political right.

12:41.560 --> 12:44.757
But no links to us,
no baggage.

12:45.720 --> 12:47.836
No overt position on guns.

12:49.280 --> 12:50.508
And you

12:51.320 --> 12:54.517
will build it up,
you will drive its agenda,

12:54.600 --> 12:57.398
and slowly but surely,

12:58.240 --> 13:00.151
you will turn those members

13:00.480 --> 13:03.916
into paid-up guardians
of the Second Amendment.

13:23.320 --> 13:24.958
So, what? Um...

13:25.040 --> 13:27.508
Mothers For A Safer America...

13:27.600 --> 13:30.592
Achieved by making sure

13:30.680 --> 13:32.910
every last citizen is
armed to the teeth?

13:33.200 --> 13:34.200
Liz?

13:34.400 --> 13:36.311
Jesus, is this the reputation
I've garnered?

13:36.400 --> 13:38.311
Gold medalist
in ethical limbo?

13:39.240 --> 13:41.834
I see no ethical problem
with reframing an issue.

13:42.080 --> 13:44.753
Trying to win the female vote
by taking the gun lobby

13:44.840 --> 13:46.956
and dressing it up
in a frilly pink frock,

13:47.040 --> 13:48.075
it is so crude,

13:48.160 --> 13:50.360
it could only have originated
in a room full of old men.

13:50.400 --> 13:51.400
Well, it didn't!

13:55.000 --> 13:56.479
This is my own idea.

13:57.320 --> 14:00.710
Well, my advice
is to kill it in utero.

14:01.160 --> 14:02.718
You'll need more
than the trite wisdom

14:02.800 --> 14:04.074
that we value security

14:04.160 --> 14:06.594
to get us behind your views
on the Second Amendment.

14:14.560 --> 14:15.879
Well, the fact remains

14:16.000 --> 14:17.520
that when it comes
to the female voter,

14:18.000 --> 14:19.638
our numbers need to be better.

14:25.240 --> 14:26.389
I see.

14:27.440 --> 14:29.317
Well, why don't I take
a look at the numbers

14:29.400 --> 14:30.992
and then we'll proceed
from there?

14:33.040 --> 14:34.176
Who the hell
does she think she is?

14:34.200 --> 14:35.315
It can be spun.

14:35.400 --> 14:36.680
For the purpose of
gaining trust,

14:36.720 --> 14:38.136
it may've been
the right tactical move.

14:38.160 --> 14:40.549
And do you believe,
for one nanosecond,

14:40.640 --> 14:42.596
that was at the forefront
of her mind

14:42.680 --> 14:44.160
when she told him
to take his business

14:44.480 --> 14:45.993
and shove it up
his gun barrel?

14:46.080 --> 14:47.080
Candice!

14:47.280 --> 14:48.918
I want Sloane
in my office now!

14:50.800 --> 14:51.994
She's good, isn't she?

14:52.240 --> 14:53.559
You'll look at the numbers?

14:54.360 --> 14:55.509
I'm sure the president

14:55.600 --> 14:58.478
of one of the most powerful
groups on the Hill

14:58.560 --> 15:00.232
will be honored
that Her Majesty

15:00.320 --> 15:02.754
has agreed to look
at the fucking numbers!

15:04.600 --> 15:05.953
What's going on with you?

15:06.040 --> 15:07.837
The current system
is so porous, it floats.

15:07.920 --> 15:09.751
I don't remember
you caring, ever,

15:09.840 --> 15:11.671
one way or another about guns!

15:11.760 --> 15:13.398
My position solidified
somewhere

15:13.480 --> 15:15.311
between Columbine
and Charleston.

15:15.600 --> 15:17.397
Come on, George,
any head-case,

15:17.520 --> 15:19.875
felon or terrorist can
buy an assault rifle

15:19.960 --> 15:21.359
from a gun show, the Internet,

15:21.480 --> 15:23.914
or his buddy
at the Bowl-O-Rama

15:24.000 --> 15:26.468
without so much as an ID.

15:26.680 --> 15:27.856
Heaton-Harris
puts a stop to that.

15:27.880 --> 15:29.791
Christ, Liz,
this is the gun lobby.

15:29.880 --> 15:30.949
Do you have any idea

15:31.040 --> 15:32.680
how long I've been trying
to reel them in?

15:33.320 --> 15:34.548
No.

15:34.640 --> 15:35.709
Something happened.

15:36.160 --> 15:38.720
Someone you know
was the victim of a gun crime.

15:38.800 --> 15:41.155
Nonsense.
I just formed an opinion.

15:41.440 --> 15:43.670
You're the champion
of the free market.

15:44.200 --> 15:46.077
You abhor frivolous
government intervention...

15:46.160 --> 15:47.309
I would hardly categorize

15:47.400 --> 15:48.776
responsible gun laws
as frivolous...

15:48.800 --> 15:49.915
Indonesians!

15:50.440 --> 15:53.876
For Christ's sake,
you rep Indonesians!

15:54.160 --> 15:55.752
To stop our government
from looting

15:55.840 --> 15:57.239
one of their
few sources of income.

15:57.320 --> 15:58.673
And what is wrong
with Indonesia?

15:58.760 --> 15:59.816
We're about to
secure Al Jacobs

15:59.840 --> 16:01.114
with a field trip there.

16:01.200 --> 16:02.713
Is that a promise or a threat?

16:03.160 --> 16:04.559
I can just picture
the good Senator

16:04.640 --> 16:06.039
being boiled in a cauldron

16:06.120 --> 16:08.395
with all these natives
dancing around him.

16:08.840 --> 16:11.479
Get back to
your Fortune 500 clients.

16:11.720 --> 16:13.915
Your colorful interventions
are the cause of

16:14.000 --> 16:16.753
a lot of industry backchat
this firm could do without.

16:16.840 --> 16:18.717
I work on behalf of
causes I believe in.

16:18.800 --> 16:20.153
That's how I sleep at night.

16:20.360 --> 16:21.918
You don't sleep at night.

16:23.080 --> 16:25.389
You sit and obsess
about winning,

16:25.760 --> 16:27.239
no matter the cause.

16:28.320 --> 16:29.673
Those little pills
in your purse

16:29.800 --> 16:31.472
are not the kind that
lull you to sleep.

16:32.040 --> 16:33.951
The only reason you

16:34.040 --> 16:38.238
and your team of gum-chewing
ragamuffins are here

16:38.680 --> 16:42.036
is that your arrogant pranks
might generate enough buzz

16:42.120 --> 16:44.270
to attract clients
like Bill Sandford.

16:44.800 --> 16:48.793
Meaning, if you don't dedicate
yourself to his cause,

16:49.200 --> 16:51.350
this firm won't have
any use for you.

16:55.360 --> 16:58.511
Now go away,
look into those numbers,

16:59.520 --> 17:01.272
and start getting
women into guns.

17:06.280 --> 17:09.272
- Any dizziness? Nausea?
- No.

17:09.360 --> 17:11.999
That's what you always say.

17:12.080 --> 17:13.513
Doctor, I'm fine.

17:13.600 --> 17:15.096
If my insurance company
weren't such sticklers,

17:15.120 --> 17:16.880
we wouldn't even be having
this conversation.

17:16.920 --> 17:18.280
What time are you
getting to sleep?

17:18.560 --> 17:19.629
I sleep a lot, it varies.

17:20.000 --> 17:21.797
What time did you get to
sleep last night?

17:23.040 --> 17:24.268
Did you get any sleep at all?

17:24.360 --> 17:25.509
These are busy times.

17:25.600 --> 17:27.875
You don't need
a doctor to tell you

17:27.960 --> 17:29.880
that you're working yourself
into an early grave.

17:30.360 --> 17:31.554
The long hours...

17:31.640 --> 17:32.816
Okay, when you
called me just now,

17:32.840 --> 17:34.068
what number did you dial?

17:34.160 --> 17:35.229
Your home number.

17:35.520 --> 17:36.856
Cell is off,
cocoa is on the stove,

17:36.880 --> 17:38.074
book is at my bedside.

17:38.200 --> 17:39.679
I'll be asleep
in under two hours.

17:40.000 --> 17:41.479
Thanks for calling, Doctor.

17:41.560 --> 17:42.816
In the Republican party,

17:42.840 --> 17:44.240
he can help you out
in California...

17:44.680 --> 17:45.874
Okay!

17:46.000 --> 17:47.319
Good, welcome.

17:49.400 --> 17:51.072
Yes! Yeah.

17:51.400 --> 17:52.992
I want you to meet
Senator Davidson.

17:54.080 --> 17:56.992
Yes. I appreciate you coming
to every fundraiser.

17:57.440 --> 17:58.873
Yeah, I'll be right back.

18:27.680 --> 18:29.318
Hello! I expect to
see you next time.

18:29.400 --> 18:30.753
Yes. That would be great.

18:31.000 --> 18:32.353
Yes, nice to see you.

18:43.600 --> 18:44.874
Early night?

18:46.080 --> 18:48.389
If you're looking for a quote,
you're wasting your time.

18:49.040 --> 18:50.496
I've just watched you
extricate yourself

18:50.520 --> 18:51.669
from three conversations

18:51.760 --> 18:53.760
to use the ladies' room
in the space of 30 minutes.

18:53.800 --> 18:56.553
You busted me.
I'm incontinent. Write it up.

18:58.000 --> 18:59.035
I hope I'm wrong,

18:59.120 --> 19:00.696
but one might think
you're sick of this town.

19:00.720 --> 19:03.029
You from the Post?
How did you get in?

19:03.160 --> 19:04.720
I'd just like five minutes
of your time.

19:04.760 --> 19:05.760
Fine.

19:05.840 --> 19:08.115
Walk to my car is three,
get to the point.

19:09.040 --> 19:10.616
The word on the Hill
is that the gun lobby

19:10.640 --> 19:11.993
approached you
over Heaton-Harris

19:12.080 --> 19:13.229
and you refused.

19:13.960 --> 19:15.951
I don't comment on
"word on the Hill."

19:16.040 --> 19:17.519
I know the only way
you'd do that

19:17.600 --> 19:19.318
is if you support the bill.

19:19.400 --> 19:20.719
That's quite a story.

19:21.040 --> 19:22.678
Turning down
a prized client because

19:22.760 --> 19:24.352
you can't accept
what they stand for.

19:25.040 --> 19:27.315
Elizabeth Sloane, the
conviction lobbyist. Who knew?

19:27.400 --> 19:29.320
I said, get to the point.

19:30.120 --> 19:32.315
Will you admit
the present system is broken?

19:32.440 --> 19:34.271
I remain committed
to the Second Amendment.

19:34.840 --> 19:36.751
Dildos are illegal in Texas,

19:36.840 --> 19:38.796
but Joe Public can
walk into a sports store

19:38.880 --> 19:40.154
and walk out with a shotgun.

19:40.280 --> 19:41.793
That would explain
the low rate

19:41.880 --> 19:43.438
of dildo-related
murders in Texas.

19:45.120 --> 19:46.872
Okay, it wasn't that funny.

19:47.640 --> 19:48.993
What do you want?

19:49.080 --> 19:50.308
Your quote.

19:52.280 --> 19:54.271
Fine. A conviction lobbyist

19:54.360 --> 19:56.954
need only believe
in their ability to win.

19:59.280 --> 20:00.395
That's a keeper.

20:01.440 --> 20:03.112
One more thing,
off the record.

20:03.200 --> 20:04.496
- Mmm-hmm.
- What do you know about

20:04.520 --> 20:06.256
- the gun lobby's opponents?
- The Brady Campaign?

20:06.280 --> 20:08.256
I know they're going to lose
because their total budget

20:08.280 --> 20:09.536
is less than what
the gun lobby pays

20:09.560 --> 20:10.600
to get their shoes shined.

20:11.240 --> 20:12.958
What about their lobbyists,
Peterson Wyatt?

20:14.120 --> 20:16.475
They're a boutique bipartisan
Government Affairs agency.

20:16.600 --> 20:19.956
"Boutique" is a euphemism
for "little fish."

20:20.040 --> 20:22.315
"Bipartisan" denotes
a bunch of hippies in suits.

20:22.800 --> 20:24.313
Do you know anything
about their CEO?

20:24.440 --> 20:25.555
Guy named Schmidt?

20:25.640 --> 20:26.959
No, never heard of him.

20:27.120 --> 20:29.554
But if the firm is built
in his image,

20:29.640 --> 20:30.840
I'm sure he's a simpering wuss

20:30.920 --> 20:32.478
with a Ph.D in
style-over-substance.

20:32.600 --> 20:33.600
Got it.

20:34.800 --> 20:36.631
I never introduced myself,
by the way.

20:37.560 --> 20:38.834
My name's Rodolfo Schmidt,

20:39.840 --> 20:40.989
CEO of Peterson Wyatt.

20:44.160 --> 20:45.160
What's the matter?

20:45.240 --> 20:46.440
Am I not simpering
hard enough?

20:47.000 --> 20:48.228
Your firm's 12 years old,

20:48.320 --> 20:49.976
I'd think your name
would be Peterson or...

20:50.000 --> 20:51.399
What...

20:51.840 --> 20:53.273
What is this about?

20:54.000 --> 20:55.433
You're pro-Heaton-Harris.

20:55.520 --> 20:56.520
It's an open secret

20:56.600 --> 20:57.976
you're at war with
your firm's leadership.

20:58.000 --> 20:59.353
The Brady Campaign wants you

20:59.440 --> 21:00.839
to lead the fight
to pass the bill.

21:01.160 --> 21:02.832
You'd run defense
out of our office.

21:02.960 --> 21:04.279
When it's over,

21:04.360 --> 21:06.191
you can choose from
any of the D.C. behemoths

21:06.440 --> 21:07.668
lining up for your signature.

21:10.680 --> 21:14.229
This is Peterson Wyatt's quote
for your services.

21:19.880 --> 21:21.677
I don't know
if I should be flattered

21:21.800 --> 21:22.869
or insulted, Mr. Schmidt,

21:23.000 --> 21:25.275
but you clearly have
the wrong opinion of me.

21:25.800 --> 21:27.280
I think my opinion
of you is right on.

21:27.880 --> 21:29.960
Don't tell me you don't want
to take a swing at this.

21:30.000 --> 21:31.149
Goodbye, Mr. Schmidt.

21:32.520 --> 21:33.555
Where's your car?

21:33.640 --> 21:35.756
Should be at the valet by now.
I don't drive.

22:11.160 --> 22:12.559
Hi, Jane?

22:13.080 --> 22:14.240
Yeah, I know what time it is.

22:14.760 --> 22:16.034
Listen...

22:16.920 --> 22:18.512
If, uh, Socrates never
wrote anything,

22:19.400 --> 22:21.231
how is it anyone's
ever heard of him?

22:23.760 --> 22:24.954
Look, we need a meeting.

22:27.600 --> 22:28.736
Where are they putting
Senator Jacobs?

22:28.760 --> 22:29.760
The Lombok Lodge?

22:29.840 --> 22:30.909
Yes.

22:31.040 --> 22:32.439
- It's on the beach?
- Yes.

22:32.600 --> 22:33.794
Good.

22:34.120 --> 22:35.736
This goes off to
the Senate Ethics Committee.

22:35.760 --> 22:36.896
Once they authorize
the travel,

22:36.920 --> 22:38.035
Jacobs is on a plane.

22:38.120 --> 22:40.031
- Is that okay?
- It's fine.

22:40.120 --> 22:42.270
- Technically, I mean?
- Don't worry about it.

22:42.400 --> 22:44.277
It's just... As lobbyists,
we can't be involved

22:44.400 --> 22:46.516
in arranging overseas travel
for members of Congress.

22:47.280 --> 22:49.191
I read ethics regs when
I want to look busy.

22:49.520 --> 22:51.096
If you weren't just
pretending to be busy,

22:51.120 --> 22:52.216
you'd know that the workaround

22:52.240 --> 22:53.336
is to get this
to the non-profit,

22:53.360 --> 22:55.555
have them sign and file
with the Ethics Committee.

22:55.640 --> 22:57.358
Do I seem unduly concerned?

22:57.880 --> 22:58.949
Okay.

22:59.040 --> 23:01.554
George told me
what happened with Sandford.

23:01.640 --> 23:02.993
- Mmm.
- Are you retarded?

23:03.440 --> 23:05.400
Why are you eating
a chocolate cake for breakfast?

23:05.640 --> 23:07.198
- Have you no shame?
- It's a muffin.

23:07.800 --> 23:09.552
You never had
a muffin for breakfast?

23:09.640 --> 23:10.868
A muffin, let's see.

23:10.960 --> 23:13.633
Eggs, milk, flour, sugar,
cocoa powder, chocolate.

23:13.720 --> 23:15.676
That sounds exactly like
a cake, but of course,

23:16.080 --> 23:17.718
no civilized person
would ever eat

23:17.800 --> 23:19.313
a chocolate cake
for breakfast.

23:19.760 --> 23:20.909
You've lost your mind.

23:21.000 --> 23:22.558
Franklin,
are you getting this?

23:22.640 --> 23:23.920
'Cause I'm really
talking to you.

23:23.960 --> 23:24.995
Huh?

23:25.120 --> 23:26.456
Shmallow Cakes
aren't really cakes.

23:26.480 --> 23:28.152
They're marshmallow
paste sandwiched

23:28.280 --> 23:29.816
between two cookies
covered in chocolate.

23:29.840 --> 23:31.239
And while our tax code
deems cakes

23:31.680 --> 23:33.830
luxury items
and hits them harder,

23:34.160 --> 23:36.469
cookies are obviously
necessities,

23:36.640 --> 23:37.789
and therefore exempt.

23:38.120 --> 23:39.394
- Are you getting this?
- What?

23:39.520 --> 23:41.511
Have Shmallow Cakes
re-designated as cookies,

23:41.640 --> 23:43.915
argue cake in the name
is merely marketing puff.

23:44.160 --> 23:45.513
You'll need evidence in court,

23:45.640 --> 23:47.080
but get a team
of scientists to opine

23:47.160 --> 23:52.632
that they are in fact 80%
cookie and zero percent cake.

23:53.200 --> 23:54.349
That's how you win.

23:54.800 --> 23:56.136
You knew that
all along?

23:56.160 --> 23:57.832
You would have
got there eventually.

23:57.920 --> 23:59.096
Then why are you
telling me this?

23:59.120 --> 24:00.519
In case you're not
coming with me.

24:04.520 --> 24:06.112
What's going on?

24:06.200 --> 24:07.349
All right, everyone.

24:07.440 --> 24:08.496
I called you here
to announce that,

24:08.520 --> 24:09.520
effective immediately,

24:09.640 --> 24:11.710
I am leaving Cole Kravitz

24:11.840 --> 24:13.353
and starting work
as lead consultant

24:13.480 --> 24:15.550
for the Brady Campaign
at Peterson Wyatt.

24:15.800 --> 24:18.394
I've secured positions
for everyone in this room

24:18.720 --> 24:20.551
without change to
your current compensation.

24:21.840 --> 24:23.114
So, who's with me on this?

24:23.200 --> 24:26.875
I just spent the last hour
wiping your shit

24:27.200 --> 24:28.428
off Bill Sandford's shoes,

24:29.560 --> 24:31.232
assuring him that
you're the right lady

24:31.320 --> 24:32.719
to broaden his membership!

24:33.520 --> 24:35.556
We're inches from
a green fucking light!

24:35.800 --> 24:37.800
So, you're saying I should
put you down as a maybe?

24:40.240 --> 24:42.470
You can't possibly win this!

24:43.360 --> 24:44.793
Who's with me?

24:52.080 --> 24:53.115
I'm with you.

24:53.480 --> 24:55.835
Whoa, whoa, Ross,
hey, come on, I need you.

24:55.920 --> 24:57.069
She needs me more.

24:57.320 --> 24:58.594
Alex?

24:59.600 --> 25:00.669
Lauren?

25:03.360 --> 25:05.555
The fuck is this?
Jerry Maguire?

25:05.920 --> 25:07.035
You've seen Jerry Maguire?

25:08.560 --> 25:09.754
Guns frighten me.

25:13.440 --> 25:16.273
So, Sloane and Co.
versus Connors and who else?

25:18.360 --> 25:21.670
Mmm. O'Hara, Wickman,
Moore, the God Squad.

25:22.040 --> 25:23.155
Ramirez,

25:25.280 --> 25:26.952
how many Tec-9s
do you own again?

25:27.040 --> 25:28.200
Enough to defend my property.

25:28.920 --> 25:30.433
Plus two more
to piss off the lefties.

25:31.800 --> 25:32.800
All right, Jane,

25:32.920 --> 25:34.416
contact Rodolfo Schmidt
at Peterson Wyatt,

25:34.440 --> 25:36.320
and tell him there's
a total of six coming over.

25:38.560 --> 25:39.834
I count five.

25:40.800 --> 25:42.279
Mathematician
you are not.

25:43.040 --> 25:44.189
Who said I was coming?

25:44.280 --> 25:45.474
I did. Call Rodolfo.

25:46.120 --> 25:47.269
What if I'm staying?

25:47.960 --> 25:49.712
Jesus, now is not
the time to develop

25:50.120 --> 25:51.519
a sense of humor, Jane.

25:51.760 --> 25:53.591
That's good, 'cause I'm not.

25:57.400 --> 25:59.038
Seriously, kid, go.

25:59.640 --> 26:00.709
I could care less.

26:03.320 --> 26:04.594
You were right before.

26:05.000 --> 26:06.558
About post-grad.
Maybe it is a cop-out.

26:06.640 --> 26:08.437
I'm at one of the best firms
in the city.

26:09.640 --> 26:11.676
Your reputation
might survive a move

26:11.840 --> 26:15.628
to some third-tier outfit
to fight a losing battle.

26:16.640 --> 26:18.153
Mine won't.

26:18.240 --> 26:19.275
No shit.

26:20.000 --> 26:21.319
I take it back.

26:23.000 --> 26:25.992
I've learned a lot from you
these last couple years, Liz.

26:26.840 --> 26:28.159
I'll miss you.

26:29.160 --> 26:30.832
The 3:00 a.m. wake-up calls?

26:31.240 --> 26:32.673
Not so much.

26:34.160 --> 26:36.151
You've obviously learned
more than you let on.

26:36.640 --> 26:38.676
You've shown more ambition
in the last 60 seconds

26:38.760 --> 26:40.990
than I've seen
in the prior two years,

26:41.120 --> 26:42.314
but you are delusional

26:43.000 --> 26:45.036
if you think you can
survive without me.

26:46.040 --> 26:47.519
If we butt heads on this,

26:47.600 --> 26:49.795
don't think I'll show you
any compassion.

26:51.520 --> 26:52.748
And with that in mind,

26:52.880 --> 26:55.553
I will give you a final
opportunity to reconsider.

27:08.320 --> 27:11.198
All right. I'm off to say my goodbye
to the money-man.

27:11.560 --> 27:13.790
When this town guts you
like a trout

27:13.880 --> 27:15.950
and chokes you
with your own entrails,

27:16.040 --> 27:18.110
don't come sniveling to me.

27:19.880 --> 27:21.393
We'll come back

27:21.560 --> 27:23.596
to the Asian Republic
of Indonesia later,

27:25.360 --> 27:27.555
but, you see, what troubles me

27:27.640 --> 27:30.712
is the amount
of influence you had.

27:31.040 --> 27:32.917
We've seen communications

27:33.040 --> 27:35.713
from senior figures
in Washington

27:36.240 --> 27:39.755
who feared that you,
a lobbyist,

27:40.400 --> 27:43.073
could destroy their careers
with a snap of your fingers.

27:45.240 --> 27:46.832
Is this reputation something

27:46.920 --> 27:48.273
you've cultivated,
Miss Sloane?

27:50.240 --> 27:51.468
Upon the advice of counsel,

27:51.560 --> 27:53.600
I must respectfully decline
to answer your question,

27:53.760 --> 27:55.480
based on my rights
under the Fifth Amendment

27:55.520 --> 27:57.351
to the United States
Constitution.

27:57.680 --> 27:59.272
You see, it's bad enough
one person

27:59.360 --> 28:01.191
having that much influence,

28:01.680 --> 28:05.434
but if they're out of control,
if she has a problem,

28:06.600 --> 28:08.830
an addiction, well,

28:10.120 --> 28:12.315
it would be like the ship
of American politics

28:12.720 --> 28:14.119
is being steered by a drunk.

28:16.760 --> 28:19.797
Do you, or have you ever had,

28:20.200 --> 28:22.111
any problems with
substance abuse?

28:22.800 --> 28:24.119
Upon the advice of counsel,

28:24.200 --> 28:26.634
I must respectfully decline
to answer your question,

28:26.760 --> 28:28.480
based on my rights
under the Fifth Amendment

28:28.600 --> 28:29.920
to the United States
Constitution.

28:30.440 --> 28:32.120
I understand you have difficulty sleeping?

28:36.120 --> 28:39.112
We subpoenaed medical records.

28:39.440 --> 28:43.638
You're a long-time sufferer
from chronic insomnia.

28:45.320 --> 28:48.471
You regularly work
over 16 hours a day.

28:48.600 --> 28:51.592
But you can't get off
to sleep. Is this accurate?

28:53.000 --> 28:55.309
Upon the advice of counsel,
I respectfully...

28:55.400 --> 28:57.630
I must respectfully decline
to answer your question,

28:57.760 --> 28:59.637
based on my rights under

28:59.720 --> 29:01.400
the Fifth Amendment
of the United States...

29:01.440 --> 29:02.634
To the Constitution.

29:02.800 --> 29:04.074
Whatever.

29:04.680 --> 29:05.680
You were prescribed

29:06.080 --> 29:10.312
multiple courses
of benzodiazepines,

29:10.960 --> 29:12.096
but according to
the deposition

29:12.120 --> 29:13.394
of one of our witnesses,

29:13.520 --> 29:16.592
you've been procuring,
off-prescription,

29:16.680 --> 29:18.750
a course of psycho-stimulants,

29:19.160 --> 29:23.597
with the aim of keeping you
awake a little longer.

29:24.360 --> 29:25.793
Is this true?

29:26.800 --> 29:28.199
Miss Sloane?

29:30.480 --> 29:31.560
Upon the advice of counsel,

29:31.600 --> 29:33.416
I must respectfully decline
to answer your question,

29:33.440 --> 29:34.976
based on my rights
under the Fifth Amendment

29:35.000 --> 29:36.672
to the United States
Constitution.

29:38.520 --> 29:40.670
Okay. Getting back
to this business

29:40.760 --> 29:42.352
of the Asian Republic
of Indonesia...

29:42.480 --> 29:43.959
I am not a drug addict,

29:44.040 --> 29:46.190
and this line of questioning
has no revel...

29:46.280 --> 29:47.793
Relevance in this case.

29:47.880 --> 29:49.518
My medication doesn't
affect my judgment

29:49.640 --> 29:51.278
any more than
a double espresso.

29:51.360 --> 29:53.555
And speaking of intoxication,

29:53.680 --> 29:55.113
I can recite from memory

29:55.200 --> 29:57.634
a list of upstanding,
elected Senators

29:57.720 --> 30:01.030
who voted on legislation
while severely inebriated.

30:01.360 --> 30:03.555
And just so you know,
I think, by now,

30:03.880 --> 30:05.029
we are fully aware,

30:05.160 --> 30:07.310
and in no danger
of forgetting,

30:07.400 --> 30:09.630
that Indonesia is a republic,

30:09.720 --> 30:13.554
which happens to be situated
on the continent of Asia.

30:15.720 --> 30:16.869
Miss Sloane.

30:19.560 --> 30:21.073
Welcome to the party.

30:26.480 --> 30:27.913
Five years.

30:30.680 --> 30:31.874
Was it really worth it?

30:32.600 --> 30:34.397
- Five years minimum.
- What's five years?

30:34.560 --> 30:37.757
All for some puerile quip
about Indonesia being in Asia.

30:39.200 --> 30:42.510
Can't you see that whole
construct was designed to...

30:42.600 --> 30:43.600
And it worked.

30:44.400 --> 30:46.072
Are you gonna tell me
what five years is?

30:46.240 --> 30:47.355
You fell for it.

30:48.040 --> 30:49.678
The smartest operative
on the Hill

30:49.760 --> 30:51.352
just got played
by Grampa Simpson!

30:51.440 --> 30:52.536
Is it how long
this conversation's

30:52.560 --> 30:53.595
gonna feel like?

30:53.680 --> 30:56.592
It's the going rate for
perjury before Congress.

30:56.680 --> 30:57.920
Now you've
thrown out the Fifth,

30:57.960 --> 30:59.359
anyone who wants you
in the ground,

30:59.440 --> 31:01.874
and that's a lot of people,
they're hard at work

31:01.960 --> 31:04.190
dedicating their creative
and intellectual efforts

31:04.280 --> 31:05.599
to catching you in a lie.

31:05.720 --> 31:08.109
Well, what if I just
stay silent?

31:08.520 --> 31:10.112
Well, that's a great idea.

31:10.200 --> 31:11.856
Shit, why didn't your lawyer
think of that?

31:11.880 --> 31:13.029
If I refuse to answer...

31:13.120 --> 31:14.189
They'll throw you in jail

31:14.280 --> 31:15.713
- for contempt of Congress!
- Shh!

31:16.440 --> 31:18.351
You've just blown
this thing wide open!

31:18.480 --> 31:19.549
Calm down, Daniel.

31:19.960 --> 31:21.440
You're starting
to look like you care.

31:21.480 --> 31:22.629
No.

31:22.760 --> 31:23.760
I don't care about you

31:23.800 --> 31:25.080
any further than
I can throw you.

31:25.800 --> 31:28.234
I work for the one ethical
lobbying practice on the Hill,

31:28.320 --> 31:30.550
and I wind up defending
the poster child

31:30.640 --> 31:32.039
for the most morally bankrupt

31:32.160 --> 31:33.360
profession since
faith healing.

31:37.480 --> 31:39.296
Your car's downstairs.

31:39.320 --> 31:42.995
Go home, stare at the ceiling,
get ready to be crucified.

31:44.600 --> 31:46.216
I know I don't have
the most stellar record

31:46.240 --> 31:47.309
in heeding your advice...

31:47.440 --> 31:48.998
Don't perjure yourself!

31:56.160 --> 31:58.240
Too bad things didn't
pan out with Elizabeth.

31:59.600 --> 32:01.158
Oh, we have other options.

32:02.000 --> 32:03.831
What the hell is
"Amish chicken"?

32:03.960 --> 32:05.518
A marketing exercise?

32:05.840 --> 32:08.400
No, we'll just try and find
ourselves another lobbyist.

32:09.920 --> 32:12.275
I was talking about
the Amish chicken.

32:12.840 --> 32:13.840
Oh.

32:14.200 --> 32:15.599
She's your enemy now.

32:16.760 --> 32:18.591
I invited you here
because nobody

32:18.680 --> 32:20.830
is better placed
to neutralize her than us.

32:21.000 --> 32:22.160
We worked together for years.

32:22.800 --> 32:24.518
We know exactly
how she operates.

32:28.360 --> 32:29.873
Oh, that is just
a regular bird

32:29.960 --> 32:31.336
raised in Amish country,
by the way.

32:31.360 --> 32:32.360
Ah.

32:33.160 --> 32:35.120
It tastes better because
it can't use Google, huh?

32:38.880 --> 32:40.176
Look, there's over
five million of us.

32:40.200 --> 32:41.349
And we're armed.

32:42.160 --> 32:44.116
We've beaten
this kind of bill before,

32:44.200 --> 32:45.679
we'll beat it again.

32:46.280 --> 32:47.952
They'll make a lot of noise,

32:48.040 --> 32:51.191
they'll wave their banners,
but in the end

32:51.320 --> 32:52.514
it's so predictable.

32:53.000 --> 32:54.558
She's not predictable.

32:57.240 --> 32:59.231
She aims to surprise.

33:00.960 --> 33:02.280
She'll share things
with her team,

33:02.360 --> 33:03.560
but she won't
share everything.

33:04.080 --> 33:05.638
She'll have a plan
for certain people,

33:05.720 --> 33:07.472
but they won't know
until they're dropped

33:07.560 --> 33:08.680
right into the middle of it.

33:09.040 --> 33:10.896
There's always something
else going on with her.

33:10.920 --> 33:12.069
It's just how she works.

33:12.160 --> 33:14.196
We have a good idea
which Senators she'll go for

33:15.160 --> 33:16.388
and we can get in first.

33:17.160 --> 33:18.752
And they're vulnerable
on other members

33:18.840 --> 33:19.896
they're already counting on.

33:19.920 --> 33:21.035
Badgley, Michigan.

33:21.840 --> 33:23.876
He can bring maybe six votes.

33:24.320 --> 33:26.231
We get to him,
it's a quick win.

33:31.840 --> 33:32.909
All right.

33:33.600 --> 33:35.079
Show me some tradecraft.

33:35.920 --> 33:38.115
- Filet mignon, rare.
- Same, well done.

33:38.760 --> 33:39.954
Well done too.

33:40.240 --> 33:41.355
The Arctic char.

33:41.600 --> 33:43.238
Amish chicken salad, please.

33:46.920 --> 33:48.239
Excuse me.

33:51.520 --> 33:54.114
That kind of insight is
exactly why you're here.

33:55.600 --> 33:57.909
I'm sorry,
who closed him again?

34:16.400 --> 34:17.753
Who the hell are you?

34:18.400 --> 34:19.674
Evening, ma'am.

34:23.080 --> 34:24.798
What happened to
the usual guy? Mark.

34:26.160 --> 34:27.718
If that's his real name.

34:28.160 --> 34:29.718
Mark's moved on.

34:30.280 --> 34:31.474
Call me Forde.

34:32.760 --> 34:33.954
Is that your real name?

34:34.480 --> 34:35.549
Is to you.

34:37.160 --> 34:38.832
- How about you, gorgeous?
- Oh, God.

34:39.160 --> 34:41.151
You a politico, or one of
these corporate-types?

34:42.400 --> 34:44.550
What brings a fine lady
like you to room 904?

34:45.000 --> 34:47.468
Not the conversation.
How much you had to drink?

34:48.640 --> 34:51.074
Well, a free minibar,
I'd say not nearly enough.

34:51.160 --> 34:52.832
You're not allowed
to smoke in here.

34:54.240 --> 34:55.880
You're not allowed
to buy company in here,

34:55.920 --> 34:57.273
yet here you are.

34:57.360 --> 34:58.679
Smoke is detectable.

34:59.000 --> 35:00.831
It could draw attention.
It is unprofessional.

35:00.960 --> 35:02.188
Okay.

35:02.920 --> 35:05.036
Corporate-type. Lawyer, maybe.

35:05.120 --> 35:06.348
If we're going to proceed,

35:06.480 --> 35:08.038
I require
a certain standard of...

35:08.120 --> 35:09.314
Agency rules, lady.

35:09.760 --> 35:11.040
Payment in cash,
I'm the only one

35:11.120 --> 35:12.880
to know this little party
here ever happened.

35:13.160 --> 35:15.116
And that's with half a minibar
down my gullet.

35:18.640 --> 35:20.680
I understand if you were
looking for something else.

35:24.880 --> 35:26.233
You'll do fine.

35:27.840 --> 35:28.989
Let's get to the point.

35:32.400 --> 35:33.628
All right.

35:40.760 --> 35:42.840
Hey, I hope you guys don't
feel like you're slumming.

35:43.200 --> 35:44.553
I thought it'd be weirder.

35:44.640 --> 35:46.631
Bean bags,
couple swings, maybe.

35:46.720 --> 35:48.336
At least tell me you guys
have shower rooms.

35:48.360 --> 35:49.998
Cole Kravitz had shower rooms?

35:50.080 --> 35:51.176
Clients felt like
they needed one

35:51.200 --> 35:52.315
after 30 minutes with him.

35:52.400 --> 35:54.630
We had all the facilities,
and no time to use them.

35:54.720 --> 35:55.720
This'll do fine.

35:55.880 --> 35:57.598
The vending machine
downstairs is weird.

35:57.920 --> 35:59.040
Wouldn't give me my beverage

35:59.080 --> 36:00.640
until I told it my gender
and age range.

36:00.760 --> 36:02.159
The vending machine
company sells

36:02.240 --> 36:03.456
our personal details
to Big Advertising.

36:03.480 --> 36:05.311
I already posted a complaint.

36:05.400 --> 36:06.594
It's okay, I just lied.

36:06.720 --> 36:08.233
You told it you were
an adult male?

36:08.360 --> 36:09.918
Why are you
so horrible to him?

36:10.000 --> 36:11.752
Jacobs just pulled
the Nutella Tax.

36:11.880 --> 36:13.440
- When did that happen?
- I just got it.

36:13.560 --> 36:15.560
The tax on palm oil?
You're the ones who killed it?

36:15.600 --> 36:16.669
Dead with the dodo.

36:16.760 --> 36:18.016
Along with how many
other unique species

36:18.040 --> 36:19.200
in the Indonesian rainforest?

36:19.280 --> 36:20.599
Not your greatest
analogy there.

36:21.240 --> 36:22.480
I guess it should
be up to them,

36:22.520 --> 36:24.192
I mean, it is, after all,
their country.

36:24.280 --> 36:26.256
Do you know how much pollution
their slashing and burning

36:26.280 --> 36:27.429
pumps into the atmosphere?

36:27.520 --> 36:30.353
Less than 0.2% of global
greenhouse emissions.

36:30.440 --> 36:32.590
- So, are the rumors true?
- Yes.

36:32.720 --> 36:34.278
Ross is really a woman.

36:34.760 --> 36:37.035
Is Sloane the personification
of an ice cube?

36:37.120 --> 36:38.519
She pees standing up.

36:38.600 --> 36:40.556
And, like...
I don't even do that.

36:40.800 --> 36:42.199
Do you think before you speak?

36:42.280 --> 36:43.793
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

36:43.920 --> 36:44.955
- Morning.
- Morning.

36:45.080 --> 36:47.640
I was thinking, perhaps,
we go around the table,

36:47.760 --> 36:48.954
introduce ourselves.

36:49.040 --> 36:50.632
Let's spare ourselves
the tedium.

36:50.720 --> 36:53.029
If you want to break the ice,
do it with insight.

36:53.120 --> 36:54.712
We're all here to ensure
safe passage

36:54.800 --> 36:56.950
of the Heaton-Harris Bill
into Federal law.

36:57.520 --> 36:58.794
How do we do it?

37:00.600 --> 37:01.919
Realistically, we don't.

37:02.960 --> 37:04.473
We fight as hard as we can,

37:04.600 --> 37:06.158
build a strong base
of support,

37:06.240 --> 37:07.389
so we have a better chance

37:07.480 --> 37:09.056
when they introduce
next year's Heaton-Harris,

37:09.080 --> 37:10.149
or the one after that.

37:10.240 --> 37:11.468
I didn't just move across town

37:11.600 --> 37:13.216
with the aim of losing
as slowly as possible.

37:13.240 --> 37:14.559
Name and seniority?

37:15.280 --> 37:17.316
Esme Manucharian, nine years.

37:17.440 --> 37:19.237
Manucharian,
I've heard that name.

37:19.720 --> 37:21.631
Esme's our authority
on gun control.

37:22.280 --> 37:23.416
When it comes
to facts and figures,

37:23.440 --> 37:24.475
she has no equal.

37:24.600 --> 37:25.999
You led the fight to preserve

37:26.120 --> 37:27.678
the concealed carry ban
in Illinois.

37:28.480 --> 37:29.913
Ultimately unsuccessfully,
but, yes.

37:31.080 --> 37:32.559
Okay, Esme.
Why are we going to lose?

37:33.520 --> 37:35.909
For every dollar Brady spends
on campaign contributions,

37:36.000 --> 37:37.376
you know how much
the gun lobby spends?

37:37.400 --> 37:38.600
- Thirty-eight.
- Thirty-eight.

37:39.680 --> 37:41.750
So, politicians bow
to money. But, why?

37:41.840 --> 37:43.910
It's not going into their
pocket, that'd be bribery.

37:44.000 --> 37:46.080
Like what the Indonesians
just did to Senator Jacobs?

37:46.200 --> 37:47.456
That was legal bribery

37:47.480 --> 37:48.993
for educational purposes.
But, yes.

37:49.120 --> 37:51.634
A senator's priority
isn't representing the people,

37:51.840 --> 37:53.159
it's keeping his ass
in office.

37:53.440 --> 37:54.440
That is so cynical.

37:54.520 --> 37:56.176
"Cynical" is a word
used by Pollyannas

37:56.200 --> 37:58.031
to denote an absence
of the naivety

37:58.160 --> 37:59.991
they so keenly exhibit.

38:00.360 --> 38:01.475
Wow. You settle in fast.

38:02.480 --> 38:06.109
If senators only care about
protecting their position,

38:06.480 --> 38:08.869
wouldn't that make them
slaves to public opinion?

38:09.000 --> 38:11.116
Polling data puts
a majority of Americans

38:11.200 --> 38:12.428
in favor of Heaton-Harris.

38:12.560 --> 38:14.676
And that's exactly why
you keep losing.

38:15.000 --> 38:16.816
Well, this is actually
our first crack at guns,

38:16.840 --> 38:17.875
but I take your point.

38:18.000 --> 38:19.194
What point?

38:19.320 --> 38:20.958
Public opinion is overrated.

38:21.040 --> 38:23.952
Midterm re-election rates
for senators was 82%.

38:24.040 --> 38:25.792
Voter turnout was 36.

38:25.880 --> 38:26.976
And I'll bet most of them were

38:27.000 --> 38:28.319
paid-up members
of the gun lobby.

38:28.400 --> 38:29.469
Thank you.

38:29.560 --> 38:31.312
Our opposition has created
a base of voters,

38:31.400 --> 38:32.879
vast and fanatical,

38:32.960 --> 38:34.234
who go out and vote
exclusively

38:34.360 --> 38:35.395
on the issue of guns.

38:35.480 --> 38:36.600
How do we compete with that?

38:36.680 --> 38:38.238
We build our own base
of supporters,

38:38.320 --> 38:39.456
who demonstrate a willingness

38:39.480 --> 38:42.313
to get their asses into booths
and vote against guns.

38:42.400 --> 38:44.160
What's the best indicator
of voter intention?

38:44.240 --> 38:45.309
- Money!
- Finance!

38:45.400 --> 38:46.753
That's our first prong.

38:46.840 --> 38:48.239
Grassroots action

38:48.320 --> 38:49.840
aimed squarely at
soliciting donations.

38:50.400 --> 38:52.868
Not names on a petition,
not clicks in cyberspace.

38:52.960 --> 38:54.216
Will they know
how much we're raising?

38:54.240 --> 38:56.231
Non-profits have to
report on their finances.

38:56.600 --> 38:57.999
And every
Congressional staffer

38:58.080 --> 38:59.280
watches filing day
like a hawk.

38:59.320 --> 39:00.594
While you're
out there hustling,

39:00.720 --> 39:02.153
I'll be working
influential senators

39:02.240 --> 39:03.912
who can deliver
their colleagues' votes.

39:04.000 --> 39:05.513
That's our second prong.

39:05.600 --> 39:07.158
Our third is to identify

39:07.280 --> 39:09.271
who holds sway
in target states.

39:09.400 --> 39:11.277
Employers, workers' groups.

39:11.360 --> 39:13.749
Don't just waltz into
a senator's office

39:13.840 --> 39:15.114
and make your case.

39:15.200 --> 39:16.792
Find out who they trust,

39:17.040 --> 39:19.508
who they can't afford
to piss off.

39:19.600 --> 39:22.478
Convince that person
to make your case.

39:23.440 --> 39:26.398
That is how we win.

39:32.720 --> 39:34.278
Not a driver?

39:34.840 --> 39:35.909
I can, but I don't.

39:36.720 --> 39:39.359
Well, you got further than me,
I don't even have a license.

39:39.480 --> 39:41.277
My bank account
and liberal conscience

39:41.360 --> 39:42.713
won't justify my own car.

39:43.960 --> 39:45.075
What's your excuse?

39:45.320 --> 39:47.117
To be honest, I suck at it.

39:47.480 --> 39:49.232
I took my test when I was 16.

39:49.320 --> 39:50.878
Only exam I ever failed.

39:51.120 --> 39:53.395
My instructor told me
I was reckless,

39:53.480 --> 39:55.311
I lacked due care
and attention.

39:55.800 --> 39:57.870
Knew then and there
I had a career in politics.

40:00.600 --> 40:02.318
You weren't
messing around in there.

40:03.640 --> 40:04.789
Did you know someone?

40:06.240 --> 40:07.616
Someone who was
a victim of gun violence.

40:07.640 --> 40:09.153
No, why does everyone
assume that?

40:09.840 --> 40:11.159
Strong opinions, maybe?

40:11.280 --> 40:13.056
As if I can only see
the merits of an argument

40:13.080 --> 40:14.991
when I feel the effects
personally.

40:15.480 --> 40:18.233
There was a Congressman,
I don't remember his name,

40:18.320 --> 40:20.629
his whole career
he was against gay rights,

40:21.000 --> 40:23.673
only to do a complete U-turn
when his brother came out.

40:23.800 --> 40:26.360
What a well-reasoned
basis for an opinion.

40:26.680 --> 40:28.477
Give him a gavel,
put him in a courthouse.

40:33.040 --> 40:34.040
Are you hungry?

40:40.800 --> 40:42.836
You eat here
every night?

40:43.920 --> 40:45.717
Pretty much.
Place never closes.

40:46.040 --> 40:47.359
How do you
not get bored of it?

40:48.840 --> 40:49.875
It's a necessity.

40:49.960 --> 40:52.120
It's like asking if I get
bored of going to the toilet.

40:53.520 --> 40:55.636
Okay, this is going to
sound alien to you,

40:55.720 --> 40:58.792
but food takes up an inordinate
amount of space in my head.

41:00.280 --> 41:01.554
How about guns?

41:04.120 --> 41:06.040
In doing my due diligence,
your rsum stood out.

41:06.600 --> 41:08.591
I noticed a lot of your work
pertains to firearms.

41:08.680 --> 41:10.477
I'm guessing that was
a conscious decision

41:10.560 --> 41:12.278
to steer things
in that direction.

41:13.920 --> 41:16.275
It's an issue I feel
strongly about.

41:20.760 --> 41:21.829
It's none of my business,

41:21.920 --> 41:23.320
but there was a gap
in your profile.

41:23.720 --> 41:25.631
Before Berkeley,
you attended high school

41:25.720 --> 41:27.392
in Bloomington, Indiana,
in the late '90s.

41:28.880 --> 41:30.916
The name of the school
isn't listed.

41:36.520 --> 41:37.999
Who else knows about this?

41:40.400 --> 41:42.516
Rodolfo. That's all.

41:45.280 --> 41:46.456
You can imagine
what I'm thinking.

41:46.480 --> 41:50.871
I'm sorry, Elizabeth,
but I earned my reputation.

41:52.280 --> 41:53.336
It didn't come from something

41:53.360 --> 41:54.656
that happened when
I was in high school.

41:54.680 --> 41:56.671
Even if my views did.

41:56.760 --> 41:58.376
Going public could even
weaken my standing.

41:58.400 --> 41:59.879
They'll say I'm too emotional.

42:01.120 --> 42:03.759
Anyway, the shooters
didn't even buy their guns.

42:04.840 --> 42:06.239
Heaton-Harris
wouldn't have made

42:06.320 --> 42:07.520
a shred of
difference that day.

42:08.640 --> 42:12.155
You fear a weakened standing
will damage your ability to effect change.

42:12.640 --> 42:14.471
But if acknowledging it
was the difference

42:14.560 --> 42:16.118
between winning and losing?

42:19.840 --> 42:21.637
I'd appreciate it
if you just treated me

42:21.720 --> 42:22.948
as one of the team.

42:26.320 --> 42:28.515
A highly competent one,
I can tell.

42:29.200 --> 42:30.349
We're lucky to have you.

42:34.960 --> 42:36.029
Sixty is the magic number.

42:36.120 --> 42:38.031
Sixty votes
breaks a filibuster.

42:38.120 --> 42:39.758
So, the gun lobby
wins with 41?

42:39.840 --> 42:41.353
They could win
with fewer.

42:41.440 --> 42:44.159
We need to hit 60.
Anything less doesn't cut it.

42:44.320 --> 42:45.594
Fifty-nine doesn't cut it.

42:46.280 --> 42:48.236
We need 60 senators
to show up and vote.

42:48.640 --> 42:50.392
We don't get that,
they win, period.

42:51.320 --> 42:52.514
As I was saying...

42:54.720 --> 42:56.517
That by my reckoning,
the gun lobby

42:56.600 --> 42:59.273
has 34 votes
pretty much locked.

42:59.600 --> 43:00.874
And that's this side.

43:01.320 --> 43:03.834
I'd say we have 44 locked
over here on this side.

43:04.320 --> 43:06.880
That leaves 22
that are still in play.

43:07.200 --> 43:09.509
These fine ladies and
gentlemen in the middle.

43:09.840 --> 43:11.068
Heaton-Harris, provisionally,

43:11.160 --> 43:13.151
makes it to the floor
in 84 days.

43:13.920 --> 43:15.148
The good news is,

43:15.280 --> 43:17.316
if we can lock 16,
we're over the line.

43:17.560 --> 43:18.834
I'm sorry,
that's the good news?

43:19.120 --> 43:20.678
We need 16 out of 22 votes?

43:21.080 --> 43:22.976
That's like sitting an exam
where the passing grade is...

43:23.000 --> 43:24.000
72%.

43:24.200 --> 43:25.680
And the bad news
is that the gun lobby

43:25.720 --> 43:27.233
is rich beyond
our wildest dreams?

43:27.320 --> 43:28.320
There is that.

43:28.400 --> 43:30.136
Or that it's not
a whole lot of time

43:30.160 --> 43:32.256
