56:39.760 --> 56:40.896
why would you do it
anonymously?

56:40.920 --> 56:41.955
Obvious reason.

56:42.040 --> 56:44.395
- What? Privacy?
- No.

56:44.480 --> 56:46.630
It makes you look noble
when you leak your identity.

56:46.720 --> 56:49.075
Oh, my God.
Were you born that cynical?

56:49.160 --> 56:51.116
That is just a word to
denote the absence...

56:51.200 --> 56:55.352
Of the naivety I so keenly
exhibit? Yeah, right.

56:57.040 --> 56:59.713
Back on in three, people.

56:59.800 --> 57:01.472
Since when
were you camera-shy?

57:02.200 --> 57:04.031
What happened?
You find a wrinkle?

57:04.120 --> 57:06.475
If it isn't
Bill Sandford's poodle.

57:06.760 --> 57:08.478
Let me guess,
on a tight leash,

57:08.560 --> 57:10.278
sniffing at his ass
for business?

57:10.840 --> 57:12.068
If you weren't such a joke,

57:12.160 --> 57:13.388
we'd already have
his business.

57:13.960 --> 57:15.598
So how about this?

57:15.680 --> 57:17.033
Give Mini-Me a day off,

57:17.160 --> 57:19.390
and I'll give you
a shot at the title.

57:19.480 --> 57:21.869
Live TV debate, you and me.

57:23.160 --> 57:24.195
You must be desperate

57:24.280 --> 57:25.416
if you're willing
to give me airtime.

57:25.440 --> 57:26.720
I kick your bony ass
hard enough,

57:26.760 --> 57:28.113
Bill Sandford will realize

57:28.200 --> 57:29.640
why he came to us
in the first place.

57:29.880 --> 57:31.871
Uh-uh. You need me strong
to make him worried.

57:33.160 --> 57:35.674
You're not looking so strong
after a head-on with me.

57:37.280 --> 57:39.350
All right. I'll grant you
a job interview

57:39.440 --> 57:40.793
on national television.

57:40.880 --> 57:43.474
You can show your master
what a big, tough dog you are.

57:53.320 --> 57:54.416
What we're about to discuss

57:54.440 --> 57:55.919
should only be
referred to in code

57:56.000 --> 57:57.558
in the office and over e-mail.

57:58.920 --> 58:00.911
My ex-employers aren't
beyond bugging and hacking.

58:01.320 --> 58:03.200
You think our conference room
is wearing a wire?

58:03.280 --> 58:04.880
We're gonna target
a senator from a state

58:05.040 --> 58:06.712
we have zero right to swing.

58:07.120 --> 58:08.280
Oh, please, God, don't say...

58:08.360 --> 58:10.476
Alberto Gomez,
Republican, Florida.

58:10.960 --> 58:12.109
What?

58:12.200 --> 58:13.576
I thought you were
gonna say Missouri.

58:13.600 --> 58:14.635
Florida's preposterous.

58:14.960 --> 58:16.029
I'm being optimistic.

58:16.800 --> 58:18.776
Public opinion runs against
Heaton-Harris in Florida.

58:18.800 --> 58:20.711
- Let's talk later.
- In the office?

58:21.480 --> 58:24.074
How do I register my dissent?
By semaphore?

58:24.280 --> 58:25.456
Alex, you're in charge
of ad banners,

58:25.480 --> 58:26.959
you have a 2:00 at JWT.

58:27.040 --> 58:28.758
I want two phone pitches.

58:28.840 --> 58:30.239
Clara, Brian, Lauren,
you're one.

58:30.360 --> 58:32.669
Cynthia, Esme, Franklin,
you're two.

58:32.760 --> 58:35.399
Ross, get stats to both.
Come on, get to it.

58:40.200 --> 58:41.758
What the hell
are you thinking?

58:41.840 --> 58:43.273
That you should
let me do my job.

58:43.360 --> 58:44.713
This ain't Cole Kravitz,
damn it.

58:45.520 --> 58:47.112
Our client's a non-profit,

58:47.200 --> 58:48.997
not some cashed-up
conglomerate.

58:49.640 --> 58:51.835
I'm hiding in the bushes
with my begging bowl,

58:51.920 --> 58:53.776
waiting to leap out at anyone
who looks like money,

58:53.800 --> 58:55.136
and you're getting ready
to set fire

58:55.160 --> 58:57.390
to half a million dollars
on some hare-brained...

58:59.800 --> 59:02.155
I mean this James Bond
shit's endearingly wacky,

59:02.600 --> 59:04.336
but if you think you're
seriously going to get

59:04.360 --> 59:06.191
any traction out of Florida,
you're way out.

59:06.280 --> 59:09.113
Rodolfo, it was explicit
in your pitch to lure me here

59:09.200 --> 59:10.656
that you held
a certain degree of trust

59:10.680 --> 59:12.272
in my ability
to run this campaign.

59:12.400 --> 59:13.799
George, it's me.

59:13.880 --> 59:15.154
I know what I'm doing.

59:15.280 --> 59:17.271
We need to talk about Florida.

59:17.360 --> 59:19.078
And I don't do hare-brained.

59:35.680 --> 59:37.193
Fucking A right.

59:37.480 --> 59:39.835
From the way you been
kicking my ass all morning,

59:39.920 --> 59:41.069
I'm starting to think

59:41.160 --> 59:43.310
you invited yourself here
just to kick my ass.

59:45.640 --> 59:47.995
I'm personally in favor
of Heaton-Harris.

59:48.560 --> 59:51.233
I've publicly declared,
my voters are behind me.

59:51.680 --> 59:54.956
Did you want to meet
just to kick my ass?

59:55.640 --> 59:57.756
Look,
you're sitting on six votes.

59:58.400 --> 59:59.594
Sandford's not a punk,

59:59.680 --> 1:00:01.716
he knows the opposition's
counting on them.

1:00:02.560 --> 1:00:04.198
He also knows
if they don't get them,

1:00:04.280 --> 1:00:05.793
their campaign will be over.

1:00:07.320 --> 1:00:08.673
So, what are you gonna do?

1:00:09.000 --> 1:00:10.115
Walk into my club,

1:00:10.200 --> 1:00:11.480
bend me over
a green baize table,

1:00:11.560 --> 1:00:13.551
and give me the spiel
about freedom?

1:00:14.840 --> 1:00:16.016
About how,
if the liberals get their way,

1:00:16.040 --> 1:00:17.200
in a couple of hundred years,

1:00:17.240 --> 1:00:18.832
the Second Amendment
will enshrine

1:00:18.920 --> 1:00:20.478
our rights to bear
baseball bats?

1:00:20.960 --> 1:00:22.678
No, that's the argument
you're gonna make

1:00:22.760 --> 1:00:24.398
to your friends
in the Blue Dog Coalition

1:00:24.480 --> 1:00:26.400
when you tell them
you're changing your position.

1:00:30.520 --> 1:00:32.750
Bill Sandford's thinking about
backing a new candidate.

1:00:33.760 --> 1:00:36.194
One of their own.
A real up-and-comer. Hispanic.

1:00:36.720 --> 1:00:39.393
Got offers from
eight Ivy League schools.

1:00:39.840 --> 1:00:41.068
Ivy League schools?

1:00:41.840 --> 1:00:43.432
Have you seen
my approval ratings, Pat?

1:00:43.520 --> 1:00:45.238
No, he's not running
against you.

1:00:46.720 --> 1:00:47.920
He's running against your son.

1:00:55.240 --> 1:00:57.071
The gun lobby wants
your support, Hank.

1:00:59.920 --> 1:01:01.416
They know your boy's
running for Michigan.

1:01:01.440 --> 1:01:02.839
They'll handpick an opponent.

1:01:03.480 --> 1:01:04.913
Back him to the hilt.

1:01:05.960 --> 1:01:07.712
I tried to talk Sandford
out of it, but...

1:01:07.800 --> 1:01:08.976
Bullshit, Connors,
you probably

1:01:09.000 --> 1:01:10.360
put him up to it,
you motherfucker.

1:01:10.440 --> 1:01:11.839
About those approval ratings.

1:01:13.760 --> 1:01:15.591
You can go either way.

1:01:16.840 --> 1:01:20.116
Quietly recant,
protect your son.

1:01:21.200 --> 1:01:22.633
Sandford won't forget it.

1:01:23.960 --> 1:01:26.633
You disappoint him...

1:01:28.240 --> 1:01:29.753
He won't forget that, either.

1:01:36.360 --> 1:01:37.759
So, how was Pittsburgh?

1:01:38.600 --> 1:01:40.033
What are you, a Fed?

1:01:40.800 --> 1:01:43.268
The President of the Mid-Atlantic
Association of Women

1:01:43.360 --> 1:01:45.715
in Law Enforcement called
to say thanks for lunch.

1:01:47.280 --> 1:01:48.920
I wasn't aware they were
part of our plan.

1:01:49.800 --> 1:01:50.915
It wasn't expensed.

1:01:51.000 --> 1:01:52.274
It was a 30-minute lunch.

1:01:52.360 --> 1:01:53.713
They're not
a part of our plan,

1:01:53.800 --> 1:01:55.995
which is why
it wasn't expensed.

1:01:56.120 --> 1:01:57.678
Am I not allowed
a social life?

1:01:57.800 --> 1:01:58.949
I didn't know you had one.

1:01:59.400 --> 1:02:00.799
As someone who has
her underlings

1:02:00.880 --> 1:02:02.313
root for
conversational topics.

1:02:02.400 --> 1:02:04.391
I maintain
a small circle of allies.

1:02:04.480 --> 1:02:06.198
Uh-huh. Cops and nurses?

1:02:06.680 --> 1:02:09.717
Well, I can provide a list if
you require full disclosure.

1:02:10.560 --> 1:02:13.597
So, grand unveiling.

1:02:14.720 --> 1:02:16.438
- You coming?
- We got a bigger problem.

1:02:16.720 --> 1:02:18.456
While you've been jetting
around the country for lunch,

1:02:18.480 --> 1:02:20.040
our opponents have been
doing their job.

1:02:20.400 --> 1:02:22.356
Hank Badgley,
Chairman of the Blue Dog,

1:02:22.480 --> 1:02:23.879
who controls the votes of...

1:02:24.000 --> 1:02:26.309
Six Senators, I know who
he is. He's in our pocket.

1:02:26.400 --> 1:02:27.992
Really? That what you think?

1:02:29.040 --> 1:02:31.679
He was on board,
but he just did a 180.

1:02:32.480 --> 1:02:34.118
Says he wants to wait and see.

1:02:36.000 --> 1:02:37.672
"Wait and see"
is more like a 90.

1:02:38.080 --> 1:02:39.911
We're chasing Senators
who are in play.

1:02:40.000 --> 1:02:42.195
We can't afford to lose
seven votes we had locked.

1:02:42.360 --> 1:02:43.588
We won't recover.

1:02:43.880 --> 1:02:45.757
We have him on camera
pledging support?

1:02:45.840 --> 1:02:46.840
Absolutely.

1:02:47.440 --> 1:02:49.078
Then we'll have to
make him feel it.

1:02:56.760 --> 1:02:58.079
Thank you.

1:03:04.680 --> 1:03:07.592
Alex, these banners are good.

1:03:08.560 --> 1:03:09.754
Could you say that again

1:03:09.880 --> 1:03:11.200
and sound a little
less surprised?

1:03:11.720 --> 1:03:13.392
Hold on, this can't be right.

1:03:13.800 --> 1:03:15.950
- Senator Gomez...
- We're not going to Florida.

1:03:17.160 --> 1:03:18.160
What?

1:03:19.480 --> 1:03:20.549
Florida's out.

1:03:22.000 --> 1:03:23.056
But you said that
we were going to Florida

1:03:23.080 --> 1:03:24.080
to swing Gomez...

1:03:24.160 --> 1:03:26.469
Everyone turn to Tab 9,
please.

1:03:31.920 --> 1:03:33.512
I don't have
anything at Tab 9.

1:03:47.440 --> 1:03:49.351
Security, lock down
Cynthia Green's desk.

1:03:49.440 --> 1:03:51.078
Secure her files
and her hard drives,

1:03:51.160 --> 1:03:52.400
and escort her
off the premises.

1:03:53.760 --> 1:03:54.909
Your Blackberry, now.

1:03:57.240 --> 1:03:58.639
Now!

1:04:00.840 --> 1:04:01.955
Let's go.

1:04:02.440 --> 1:04:03.759
He offered me
partnership track.

1:04:04.000 --> 1:04:05.399
Good luck with that.

1:04:05.920 --> 1:04:07.273
Clear the office.

1:04:08.360 --> 1:04:09.960
Come on, come on, come on!
Everybody out.

1:04:15.280 --> 1:04:16.640
I'll have the place
swept for taps.

1:04:17.920 --> 1:04:19.638
Sounds like James Bond
shit to me.

1:04:19.960 --> 1:04:21.473
We will talk about this later.

1:04:24.120 --> 1:04:25.917
Come on, everybody,
clear the building!

1:04:26.960 --> 1:04:28.951
Let's go! Out! Come on!

1:04:40.480 --> 1:04:41.480
I can't believe the whole

1:04:41.520 --> 1:04:43.317
Gomez-Florida thing
was a ruse.

1:04:43.480 --> 1:04:45.357
We're coming out of
left field to take Colorado

1:04:45.480 --> 1:04:48.074
before they figure out which
hole they got screwed in.

1:04:48.160 --> 1:04:49.479
How could she do that?

1:04:50.240 --> 1:04:51.912
How does someone
even think like that?

1:04:52.000 --> 1:04:53.274
Maybe in her naivety,

1:04:53.360 --> 1:04:54.920
she figured it'd be good
for her career.

1:04:57.400 --> 1:04:58.628
I wasn't talking
about Cynthia.

1:05:13.680 --> 1:05:14.749
Morning.

1:05:18.360 --> 1:05:19.634
Please take a seat.

1:05:19.720 --> 1:05:21.358
We're not saying
it can't be done.

1:05:21.840 --> 1:05:22.920
But it's risky.

1:05:23.000 --> 1:05:25.116
- We only get one shot.
- Hey!

1:05:27.440 --> 1:05:28.555
Were you followed?

1:05:28.680 --> 1:05:29.715
Evidently.

1:05:31.760 --> 1:05:32.988
Let him in.

1:05:33.360 --> 1:05:34.416
Do you solemnly swear

1:05:34.440 --> 1:05:35.496
that you will tell the truth,

1:05:35.520 --> 1:05:37.317
the whole truth,
and nothing but the truth,

1:05:37.400 --> 1:05:39.072
upon pains and penalties
of perjury?

1:05:41.240 --> 1:05:42.673
I do.

1:05:46.880 --> 1:05:48.438
State your full name, please.

1:05:48.880 --> 1:05:50.233
Well, look at this.

1:05:50.960 --> 1:05:52.757
Rodolfo Vittorio Schmidt.

1:05:54.720 --> 1:05:57.712
I'm guessing this gear
ain't for tuning my '69 Chevy?

1:05:58.360 --> 1:06:00.715
Rodolfo,
my unofficial support team.

1:06:01.960 --> 1:06:03.109
Big Sam.

1:06:03.400 --> 1:06:04.628
Little Sam.

1:06:04.920 --> 1:06:07.753
During the time that you
worked alongside Miss Sloane,

1:06:08.120 --> 1:06:09.917
did you hold any discussions

1:06:10.040 --> 1:06:11.040
pertaining to the use

1:06:11.120 --> 1:06:12.917
of illegal
surveillance techniques?

1:06:16.240 --> 1:06:17.856
So, how big
is your organization?

1:06:17.880 --> 1:06:20.519
Well, there are six of us,
four are out on assignment.

1:06:21.080 --> 1:06:22.957
- And you're ex...
- NSA.

1:06:24.160 --> 1:06:25.354
Badgley is flip-flopping.

1:06:25.440 --> 1:06:26.998
But, quickest way
to get him in line

1:06:27.080 --> 1:06:28.354
is to mine for sordid details,

1:06:28.440 --> 1:06:30.376
and then let him know
we're in possession of them.

1:06:30.400 --> 1:06:33.551
Mr. Schmidt,
did you?

1:06:34.080 --> 1:06:35.638
Yes, Senator, we did.

1:06:35.760 --> 1:06:37.796
And what means did they have
at their disposal

1:06:37.920 --> 1:06:40.388
to carry out these
surveillance practices?

1:06:40.480 --> 1:06:42.948
Standard 24-hour
video and audio surveillance,

1:06:43.080 --> 1:06:44.638
cell phone and online
account hacking,

1:06:45.080 --> 1:06:49.073
location tracking,
and, with our latest tech,

1:06:49.640 --> 1:06:52.871
close-quarters audio,
anytime, anyplace.

1:06:55.080 --> 1:06:56.920
You ever hear the expression
"Fly on the wall"?

1:06:57.360 --> 1:06:59.396
Well, meet the cutting edge
in eavesdropping.

1:07:00.920 --> 1:07:01.989
It's a cockroach.

1:07:02.120 --> 1:07:03.872
Which can be retro-fitted

1:07:03.960 --> 1:07:07.509
as a cybernetic
robo-roach with this.

1:07:09.120 --> 1:07:11.395
We glue electrodes
to its antennae,

1:07:11.480 --> 1:07:12.754
perforate the thorax,

1:07:12.880 --> 1:07:14.871
and we can control
its movement remotely.

1:07:14.960 --> 1:07:16.632
Don't call PETA, Schmidt.

1:07:16.800 --> 1:07:18.233
These guys can
crawl under doors,

1:07:18.320 --> 1:07:20.709
into crevices, bags,
completely undetected.

1:07:21.280 --> 1:07:23.635
They can go weeks without food
and still be mobile.

1:07:24.200 --> 1:07:27.829
And how did you react to
the possibility of all this?

1:07:27.960 --> 1:07:30.872
I told her it was
mind-boggling, ingenious,

1:07:30.960 --> 1:07:33.269
morally repugnant
and completely unacceptable.

1:07:33.840 --> 1:07:35.034
Boo!

1:07:35.120 --> 1:07:36.792
You're talking
about blackmailing

1:07:36.880 --> 1:07:38.518
a United States Senator.

1:07:39.880 --> 1:07:42.189
Have you any idea of the
damage if this ever came out?

1:07:42.320 --> 1:07:44.601
No more than the damage done
if we don't get Badgley back.

1:07:45.480 --> 1:07:47.232
Without prejudice
to the undoubtedly

1:07:47.320 --> 1:07:48.753
stellar job that you guys do.

1:07:49.720 --> 1:07:51.233
Our firm has certain standards

1:07:51.320 --> 1:07:53.072
below which I'm not
prepared to stoop.

1:07:55.160 --> 1:07:56.195
Let me out of here.

1:07:57.160 --> 1:07:58.229
Schmidt.

1:07:59.240 --> 1:08:00.514
Find another way.

1:08:07.200 --> 1:08:08.736
It was a rude awakening

1:08:08.760 --> 1:08:10.360
for Michigan Senator,
Hank Badgley, today

1:08:11.000 --> 1:08:14.709
as he was tailed from his home
to his workplace by this...

1:08:15.160 --> 1:08:16.559
What the fuck is that?

1:08:16.680 --> 1:08:18.432
...organized by gun safety
campaigners

1:08:18.520 --> 1:08:19.800
in response
to what they perceive

1:08:19.880 --> 1:08:21.040
as a U-turn on his support...

1:08:21.080 --> 1:08:24.550
Can you believe...
I do not fucking believe!

1:08:25.920 --> 1:08:29.037
...in the shadow
of a giant rat.

1:08:30.600 --> 1:08:33.239
It's on all of
the national news outlets.

1:08:33.360 --> 1:08:35.510
How the hell
did she manage that?

1:08:35.600 --> 1:08:38.160
She didn't. They swing
left all on their own.

1:08:38.240 --> 1:08:39.753
It has its own Twitter feed.

1:08:40.200 --> 1:08:41.200
Huh?

1:08:43.520 --> 1:08:44.839
The rat.

1:08:45.080 --> 1:08:47.799
Really, I think that
this whole rat business

1:08:47.880 --> 1:08:50.633
is little more than an
unfortunate misunderstanding.

1:08:51.040 --> 1:08:53.076
I was one of the first
members of the senate

1:08:53.200 --> 1:08:55.395
to lend my support
to Heaton-Harris.

1:08:55.480 --> 1:08:56.799
I've always maintained that

1:08:56.880 --> 1:08:58.438
the Bill is integral
to public safety,

1:08:58.560 --> 1:09:01.074
and my support for it
is unwavering.

1:09:01.240 --> 1:09:03.117
Now, I sincerely hope that

1:09:03.240 --> 1:09:04.878
we can get past
all this silliness...

1:09:04.960 --> 1:09:06.296
Th ree more
Blue Dog Senators

1:09:06.320 --> 1:09:08.470
have press conferences
scheduled for next week.

1:09:08.560 --> 1:09:09.856
Keep hammering the point

1:09:09.880 --> 1:09:11.871
that we're not arguing
for confiscation.

1:09:12.000 --> 1:09:13.353
Heaton-Harris
is about stopping...

1:09:13.440 --> 1:09:14.839
Criminals and psychopaths.

1:09:14.960 --> 1:09:16.359
Yeah, I'm a pro
at this now, Liz.

1:09:16.440 --> 1:09:18.237
I'll see you in there.

1:09:19.080 --> 1:09:21.150
So you knew there was
a leak from when?

1:09:21.240 --> 1:09:22.434
- Sorry?
- Cynthia.

1:09:22.560 --> 1:09:24.835
When did you start to
suspect there was a leak?

1:09:24.920 --> 1:09:26.717
Uh, after the UAPD fundraiser.

1:09:26.800 --> 1:09:28.552
And you had her
followed by a PI?

1:09:28.640 --> 1:09:30.278
How did you know it was her?

1:09:30.400 --> 1:09:31.719
Sorry?

1:09:31.800 --> 1:09:33.836
The leak, you had
Cynthia watched.

1:09:34.120 --> 1:09:35.599
How did you know it was her?

1:09:36.280 --> 1:09:37.838
I didn't.

1:09:39.240 --> 1:09:40.753
You had us all watched?

1:09:41.760 --> 1:09:43.079
Howdy.

1:09:44.080 --> 1:09:46.435
Cal Sneider,
banking and actuarial.

1:09:47.920 --> 1:09:49.096
I'm sure we've
been introduced,

1:09:49.120 --> 1:09:50.120
but your name escapes me.

1:09:50.320 --> 1:09:51.760
I'm sorry, you have
the wrong person.

1:09:52.000 --> 1:09:53.149
I'm pretty sure I don't.

1:09:53.360 --> 1:09:54.793
Have a good memory for faces.

1:09:55.280 --> 1:09:56.640
This one I wouldn't
readily forget.

1:09:57.440 --> 1:09:59.112
Really, Mr. Sneider,

1:09:59.520 --> 1:10:01.317
I've no idea
who you think I am.

1:10:01.440 --> 1:10:02.839
Excuse me.

1:10:11.320 --> 1:10:13.038
Uh-huh. You know
we're not really

1:10:13.120 --> 1:10:14.616
supposed to be having
this conversation, right?

1:10:14.640 --> 1:10:16.616
Half of Oregon
is protected Federal parkland.

1:10:16.640 --> 1:10:18.039
They can't develop it.

1:10:18.120 --> 1:10:19.856
So, state budgets
come from logging revenues.

1:10:19.880 --> 1:10:20.920
- I got it...
- Liz?

1:10:20.960 --> 1:10:23.080
Whatever clearing your head
looks like, this isn't it.

1:10:23.480 --> 1:10:25.277
So, loggers are
a very influential group.

1:10:25.520 --> 1:10:26.635
Excuse me!

1:10:26.720 --> 1:10:28.520
Can someone have her
makeup done, too, please?

1:10:28.560 --> 1:10:29.629
I'm not a part of this!

1:10:29.720 --> 1:10:31.256
You're a public figure
in a room full of cameras.

1:10:31.280 --> 1:10:32.395
Is that her?

1:10:34.280 --> 1:10:35.280
Liz?

1:10:35.800 --> 1:10:37.950
Hey, we have to get
Bryan on these loggers.

1:10:38.040 --> 1:10:39.256
We're on top of
the goddamn loggers!

1:10:39.280 --> 1:10:40.280
Just clear your head!

1:10:40.320 --> 1:10:41.320
One moment.

1:10:41.480 --> 1:10:42.993
Clear your head,
like I told you.

1:10:43.320 --> 1:10:44.389
Hello?

1:10:47.080 --> 1:10:49.389
- Fine.
- Ms. Sloane, welcome.

1:10:50.000 --> 1:10:52.230
Pat. Please, take a seat.

1:10:52.840 --> 1:10:54.114
I know Friday's Filing Day

1:10:54.200 --> 1:10:55.336
and your campaign
will be over,

1:10:55.360 --> 1:10:56.496
but if you're thinking
I'm gonna go easy,

1:10:56.520 --> 1:10:57.520
I can't do that.

1:10:57.920 --> 1:11:00.593
This is live TV,
so no colorful language.

1:11:00.680 --> 1:11:02.511
Bullshit
job offers to my staff,

1:11:02.600 --> 1:11:04.079
you've plumbed new depths.

1:11:04.160 --> 1:11:05.798
A giant inflatable rodent?
Please.

1:11:05.880 --> 1:11:07.080
You ruined that girl's career.

1:11:07.200 --> 1:11:10.510
All right, shut up,
the both of you. Let's go!

1:11:15.720 --> 1:11:17.836
Hello, America,
I'm Jon O'Neill,

1:11:17.960 --> 1:11:20.872
welcome to a special edition
ofThis Week In Washington.

1:11:21.360 --> 1:11:23.828
Guns! More or Less?

1:11:23.920 --> 1:11:26.798
There were 372
mass shootings last year,

1:11:26.880 --> 1:11:28.393
64 school shootings,

1:11:28.520 --> 1:11:31.398
and there are over 300
million guns in our country...

1:11:31.720 --> 1:11:33.160
You used to
work with Connors?

1:11:33.240 --> 1:11:34.434
Four years.

1:11:34.560 --> 1:11:39.270
Foul-mouthed, unexpected,
and very effective.

1:11:40.560 --> 1:11:42.994
If background checks
are to be of any use,

1:11:43.080 --> 1:11:45.753
they should apply to
all gun sales, not just some.

1:11:45.880 --> 1:11:48.075
Isn't that what Heaton-Harris
is proposing?

1:11:48.240 --> 1:11:51.835
Precisely. The bill expands
the scope of gun regulation,

1:11:51.920 --> 1:11:53.239
and it's yet another affront

1:11:53.320 --> 1:11:55.072
to Americans'
Constitutional rights.

1:11:55.160 --> 1:11:57.549
No, the bill closes
an absurd loophole

1:11:57.640 --> 1:12:00.029
which allows people
on terrorist watch-lists

1:12:00.120 --> 1:12:02.315
to buy guns without
any checks whatsoever.

1:12:02.400 --> 1:12:04.356
It's an incursion
into individual liberty

1:12:04.440 --> 1:12:05.998
by an all-powerful
government...

1:12:06.080 --> 1:12:08.548
- What, like drivers' licenses?
- Drivers' licenses?

1:12:08.840 --> 1:12:10.273
It's illegal to operate a car

1:12:10.400 --> 1:12:11.456
without going through rigorous

1:12:11.480 --> 1:12:13.118
theoretical and practical
assessments.

1:12:13.400 --> 1:12:15.470
- That's a clear constraint...
- Fugu chefs.

1:12:15.600 --> 1:12:17.480
...on the freedom of
individuals to drive cars,

1:12:17.600 --> 1:12:20.034
- or pilots to fly planes.
- Come on. Fugu chefs.

1:12:20.120 --> 1:12:22.918
You know, in Japan,
chefs train for seven years

1:12:23.000 --> 1:12:24.274
before they're
allowed to serve

1:12:24.440 --> 1:12:25.720
a poisonous blowfish
called fugu.

1:12:25.760 --> 1:12:26.795
Yes!

1:12:26.920 --> 1:12:27.976
What does any of this

1:12:28.000 --> 1:12:29.320
have to do with
background checks?

1:12:29.440 --> 1:12:30.919
Is a fair question.

1:12:31.000 --> 1:12:32.194
Does anyone in this room

1:12:32.280 --> 1:12:34.400
think the government should
abolish drivers' licenses?

1:12:34.680 --> 1:12:35.954
- That's absurd.
- Why?

1:12:36.120 --> 1:12:38.280
They're a government incursion
into individual liberty.

1:12:38.760 --> 1:12:40.796
We accept them because
they make sense.

1:12:40.960 --> 1:12:42.518
The more dangerous
the machinery,

1:12:42.600 --> 1:12:44.318
the more rigorous
the tests should be.

1:12:44.440 --> 1:12:46.192
I think we can
extend our definition

1:12:46.280 --> 1:12:48.999
of dangerous machinery
to semi-automatic firearms.

1:12:49.120 --> 1:12:51.016
Except that the Second
Amendment to the Constitution

1:12:51.040 --> 1:12:53.429
doesn't guarantee
the right to drive cars,

1:12:53.520 --> 1:12:57.115
or operate machinery or serve
blowfish for that matter.

1:12:57.200 --> 1:13:00.272
It guarantees the right
to keep and bear arms.

1:13:00.880 --> 1:13:02.438
Perhaps you haven't
read it lately.

1:13:02.520 --> 1:13:03.953
Nothing in the bill

1:13:04.040 --> 1:13:06.918
infringes the rights of the
people to keep and bear arms.

1:13:07.000 --> 1:13:08.496
The Second Amendment
was signed in a time

1:13:08.520 --> 1:13:10.397
where the average
life expectancy was 38,

1:13:10.480 --> 1:13:13.040
and it was common practice
for our Founding Fathers

1:13:13.120 --> 1:13:16.590
to resolve their differences
at dawn in a gunfight.

1:13:16.680 --> 1:13:19.638
What may have been perfectly
sensible in those alien times

1:13:20.040 --> 1:13:22.296
is wholly inadequate to solve
the problems of the present.

1:13:22.320 --> 1:13:24.197
That's not the rebuttal,
what's she doing?

1:13:24.320 --> 1:13:25.696
The United States
Constitution

1:13:25.720 --> 1:13:27.278
has stood the test of time.

1:13:27.360 --> 1:13:31.035
It's authored to confer
unimpeachable rights,

1:13:31.160 --> 1:13:32.354
which don't change depending

1:13:32.760 --> 1:13:34.432
on which way
the wind's blowing.

1:13:34.680 --> 1:13:36.398
It's so authored
with the specific intent

1:13:36.480 --> 1:13:37.674
of keeping at bay

1:13:37.760 --> 1:13:39.478
the Elizabeth Sloanes
of this world,

1:13:39.600 --> 1:13:41.496
who wanna wipe their asses
with the Constitution...

1:13:41.520 --> 1:13:42.669
Okay, let's...

1:13:42.760 --> 1:13:44.400
...and replace it
with their own judgment,

1:13:44.520 --> 1:13:45.873
because she knows better than

1:13:46.000 --> 1:13:47.672
the Founding Fathers
of this great nation.

1:13:48.000 --> 1:13:51.788
Nothing is unimpeachable,
not even the Constitution.

1:13:51.880 --> 1:13:54.075
It's ironic that the very
statement of rights

1:13:54.200 --> 1:13:55.679
you're so quick to invoke

1:13:55.760 --> 1:13:57.671
is in fact an Amendment.

1:13:58.000 --> 1:13:59.640
I may not
like it either, Elizabeth,

1:14:00.200 --> 1:14:01.679
but it's the Second Amendment.

1:14:01.760 --> 1:14:05.196
Comes right after freedom of
speech, religion, and press,

1:14:05.280 --> 1:14:07.157
and somewhere before
freedom from search

1:14:07.520 --> 1:14:09.240
and from having to testify
against yourself.

1:14:09.440 --> 1:14:10.880
They're all sort of
bunched together.

1:14:11.200 --> 1:14:12.400
It's called
the Bill of Rights.

1:14:12.800 --> 1:14:14.720
- How do you get around that?
- We don't need to.

1:14:14.960 --> 1:14:16.473
Supreme Court
already made it clear

1:14:16.560 --> 1:14:18.118
that the right to own a gun

1:14:18.200 --> 1:14:19.838
is subject to
lawful restriction.

1:14:19.920 --> 1:14:21.478
One of those
is background checks.

1:14:21.600 --> 1:14:24.717
Universal background checks
are an infringement.

1:14:25.400 --> 1:14:27.277
What part of
"shall not be infringed"

1:14:27.400 --> 1:14:28.594
don't you get?

1:14:28.720 --> 1:14:31.632
I get that that's the weakest,
most mind-numbing retort

1:14:31.920 --> 1:14:33.717
in your impoverished arsenal.

1:14:33.880 --> 1:14:35.393
Sort of a last refuge
for those

1:14:35.480 --> 1:14:36.640
with no real argument at all.

1:14:36.720 --> 1:14:37.789
You're talking about

1:14:37.880 --> 1:14:39.080
the United States
Constitution.

1:14:39.320 --> 1:14:41.675
If they could produce
a rational winning argument,

1:14:41.760 --> 1:14:43.796
I'd gladly migrate
to their side,

1:14:43.880 --> 1:14:46.758
but "because it says so
in the Constitution,

1:14:46.880 --> 1:14:50.953
"the Bible, or my horoscope,"
it's not a winning argument!

1:14:51.080 --> 1:14:52.115
It's a ripcord.

1:14:52.240 --> 1:14:54.435
An intellectual equivalent
of a yellow,

1:14:54.560 --> 1:14:57.472
pant-pissing wimp
cowering behind mommy's skirt.

1:14:57.560 --> 1:15:00.074
- Why don't we bring this back.
- No, no, no. Let's not!

1:15:00.160 --> 1:15:02.037
Why don't we ask
all the mothers out there

1:15:02.120 --> 1:15:04.839
who lost their children
to an armed sociopath,

1:15:04.920 --> 1:15:07.229
if they believe
in his unimpeachable

1:15:07.320 --> 1:15:09.675
Constitutional right
to bear arms?

1:15:09.760 --> 1:15:11.398
Why not ask the terrified girl

1:15:11.480 --> 1:15:13.516
who locked herself
in a janitor's closet

1:15:13.600 --> 1:15:14.794
at Bloomington High,

1:15:14.920 --> 1:15:16.069
forced to listen

1:15:16.160 --> 1:15:18.355
as her peers were
being massacred?

1:15:18.960 --> 1:15:20.598
Go ahead, ask her!

1:15:20.680 --> 1:15:22.955
Her name is Esme Manucharian.

1:15:25.440 --> 1:15:26.520
She's standing right there!

1:15:32.440 --> 1:15:34.032
Jesus Christ, Liz.

1:15:35.120 --> 1:15:36.553
Okay, time out!

1:15:36.640 --> 1:15:38.640
We're going to take a break,
and when we come back,

1:15:39.440 --> 1:15:41.158
maybe these two
will stop playing

1:15:41.280 --> 1:15:43.874
Patty Cake and
the gloves'll really come off.

1:15:43.960 --> 1:15:45.552
Be right back!

1:16:09.160 --> 1:16:10.752
I won't insult
your intelligence

1:16:10.840 --> 1:16:12.880
by claiming that came out
in the heat of the moment.

1:16:17.760 --> 1:16:19.193
How far back?

1:16:21.160 --> 1:16:23.390
Once I started getting
used to all the media?

1:16:26.360 --> 1:16:28.635
Okay. Day one.

1:16:30.560 --> 1:16:31.595
Wow.

1:16:37.000 --> 1:16:38.638
At dinner that night...

1:16:40.920 --> 1:16:42.638
You asked me if I'd go public

1:16:42.720 --> 1:16:45.188
if it was the difference
between victory and defeat.

1:16:48.920 --> 1:16:50.239
What if I'd said no?

1:16:52.200 --> 1:16:53.633
Would you still have done it?

1:16:54.520 --> 1:16:55.873
Probably.

1:16:57.120 --> 1:16:58.473
I was hired to win,

1:16:58.960 --> 1:17:00.393
and I have a responsibility

1:17:00.520 --> 1:17:02.158
to use whatever
resource I have.

1:17:02.960 --> 1:17:04.480
The press we're going to
get from this,

1:17:04.520 --> 1:17:06.496
it's practically a dereliction
of duty not to use it.

1:17:06.520 --> 1:17:08.272
That's it? I'm a "resource"?

1:17:08.360 --> 1:17:09.713
Professionally, yes.

1:17:12.280 --> 1:17:15.158
I understand you have
feelings, and a life,

1:17:15.240 --> 1:17:16.878
but I have no duty to them.

1:17:18.200 --> 1:17:20.509
I have a duty to the cause,
and if the two conflict,

1:17:20.600 --> 1:17:23.034
there will only
ever be one winner.

1:17:26.320 --> 1:17:28.072
Well, hooray for
straight talk.

1:17:30.160 --> 1:17:31.593
Okay.

1:17:31.720 --> 1:17:34.792
Get ready, Esme.
Network wants a statement.

1:17:34.920 --> 1:17:38.071
Re-apply your makeup.
We'll walk out arm-in-arm.

1:17:38.160 --> 1:17:39.991
We'll be brief. No questions.

1:17:40.840 --> 1:17:43.638
Tonight, we'll leave them
wanting more.

1:17:49.240 --> 1:17:50.753
First of all,

1:17:50.840 --> 1:17:52.920
I want to make it clear
that I have dedicated my life

1:17:52.960 --> 1:17:56.748
to gun safety issues because
the current system is broken.

1:17:57.160 --> 1:17:58.513
That's a rational judgment.

1:17:58.920 --> 1:18:00.239
Not an emotional one.

1:18:04.920 --> 1:18:06.319
I am a survivor

1:18:07.440 --> 1:18:10.432
of the Bloomington High School
massacre of 1998.

1:18:12.120 --> 1:18:15.237
For years, I sought to hide
the pain and the trauma,

1:18:15.320 --> 1:18:16.594
for fear of having to
relive it.

1:18:17.760 --> 1:18:19.273
But I've come to realize

1:18:20.280 --> 1:18:23.431
that the thousands of people
affected by gun violence

1:18:23.520 --> 1:18:25.954
need to stand up
and be counted.

1:18:27.440 --> 1:18:28.953
They need a representative

1:18:29.640 --> 1:18:31.995
who can speak out
for what they have endured.

1:18:32.640 --> 1:18:33.868
Let's call Sandford.

1:18:34.280 --> 1:18:35.816
Someone who can relate
their experience...

1:18:35.840 --> 1:18:37.159
There might be
life in this yet.

1:18:37.280 --> 1:18:38.554
...to the public at large.

1:19:14.160 --> 1:19:15.798
You're a piece of work,
Elizabeth.

1:19:21.680 --> 1:19:23.398
If you want to
set yourself on fire

1:19:24.000 --> 1:19:27.515
to service your need to win,
I won't protest, but Esme?

1:19:29.440 --> 1:19:30.440
The end is my concern.

1:19:30.520 --> 1:19:32.954
You liberal goody-goodies
can fret over the means.

1:19:33.080 --> 1:19:34.513
- You need me.
- The end?

1:19:34.880 --> 1:19:36.074
It disappeared over the Hill

1:19:36.200 --> 1:19:38.176
when you cocked your leg
and pissed all over the flag!

1:19:38.200 --> 1:19:41.158
Comparing the United States
Constitution to a horoscope?

1:19:42.120 --> 1:19:44.270
That's the kind of shit
the gun lobby thrives on.

1:19:45.800 --> 1:19:47.336
Or have you realized by now
we're going to lose anyway?

1:19:47.360 --> 1:19:49.430
This is more important
than my career,

1:19:49.520 --> 1:19:51.351
or Esme's unease
at fighting reporters

1:19:51.440 --> 1:19:53.040
every time she has to
take out the trash.

1:19:53.080 --> 1:19:55.355
- You're out of control.
- We're not gonna lose.

1:19:58.080 --> 1:19:59.308
What if I told you

1:20:01.720 --> 1:20:03.392
this whole strategy
was a shell game?

1:20:04.440 --> 1:20:08.228
For the benefit of the
Cynthia Greens of this firm.

1:20:09.920 --> 1:20:11.148
What are you talking about?

1:20:12.320 --> 1:20:13.799
Bill Sandford was right.

1:20:14.880 --> 1:20:17.872
Women are the
gun lobby's blind spot.

1:20:19.800 --> 1:20:22.598
A massive power base
that they don't speak to

1:20:23.240 --> 1:20:24.673
and they can't control.

1:20:25.560 --> 1:20:26.560
And?

1:20:28.280 --> 1:20:30.271
Those strange excursions
on my itinerary?

1:20:32.240 --> 1:20:35.630
Women's representative bodies,
feminist groups,

1:20:36.440 --> 1:20:37.793
female CEOs.

1:20:38.840 --> 1:20:40.319
I've talked as many as I could

1:20:40.400 --> 1:20:42.118
into brow-beating
their membership

1:20:42.240 --> 1:20:43.514
to donate to my PAC.

1:20:43.600 --> 1:20:44.600
You have a PAC?

1:20:46.360 --> 1:20:48.078
Bill Sandford's getting
a nasty surprise

1:20:48.520 --> 1:20:49.589
come filing day.

1:20:50.280 --> 1:20:51.429
How nasty are we talking?

1:20:51.920 --> 1:20:54.718
Fifteen million from over
three million donors-nasty.

1:20:56.360 --> 1:20:57.588
In one quarter?

1:21:01.120 --> 1:21:02.997
Actually, less.

1:21:04.800 --> 1:21:06.677
Unbelievable.

1:21:09.840 --> 1:21:11.080
Why are you
telling me this now?

1:21:12.480 --> 1:21:13.696
You kept this
from me all along,

1:21:13.720 --> 1:21:14.920
and you're telling me tonight?

1:21:14.960 --> 1:21:16.837
Oh, my God, I tell you
we're back in the game,

1:21:16.960 --> 1:21:18.109
and all you can say is that?

1:21:18.200 --> 1:21:19.997
You knew you were
gonna screw Esme tonight,

1:21:20.120 --> 1:21:21.656
so you kept this from me
to blindside me

1:21:21.680 --> 1:21:23.000
before I had a chance
to fire you.

1:21:23.840 --> 1:21:26.115
You have unusual insight
for a "boutique" lobbyist.

1:21:26.800 --> 1:21:28.640
You've been pulling
all the strings, all along.

1:21:30.400 --> 1:21:31.719
Lobbying is about foresight.

1:21:31.800 --> 1:21:34.075
You anticipate your opponent's
moves, you devise...

1:21:34.520 --> 1:21:36.954
I am not your
fucking opponent!

1:21:40.200 --> 1:21:42.714
Were you ever normal?

1:21:44.520 --> 1:21:45.635
As a child?

1:21:46.800 --> 1:21:49.268
Or were the twisted
thought processes in your mind

1:21:49.360 --> 1:21:50.475
hard-wired in the womb?

1:21:51.000 --> 1:21:52.558
Because I'm having
a really hard time

1:21:53.480 --> 1:21:55.357
understanding how
somebody gets to this.

1:22:00.320 --> 1:22:01.833
Guess I'm just
a piece of work.

1:22:10.000 --> 1:22:11.399
I'll see you tomorrow.

1:22:41.040 --> 1:22:42.712
You're Madeline
Elizabeth Sloane.

1:22:43.560 --> 1:22:45.915
You work in government affairs
at a communications company.

1:22:46.360 --> 1:22:47.713
Well googled.

1:22:48.760 --> 1:22:50.876
So what was that?
At the fundraiser?

1:22:51.880 --> 1:22:53.240
You pretended
like we're strangers.

1:22:53.600 --> 1:22:54.919
What did you expect?

1:22:56.840 --> 1:22:58.034
You all right?

1:22:58.600 --> 1:22:59.600
Mmm...

1:23:02.240 --> 1:23:04.310
The only person to call me
Madeline was my mother.

1:23:06.560 --> 1:23:08.835
Government affairs
and communications

1:23:08.960 --> 1:23:10.757
are just fancy words
for lobbying.

1:23:11.400 --> 1:23:13.550
And lobbying's a fancy word
for what, exactly?

1:23:13.680 --> 1:23:15.272
Outside this room,
we're strangers.

1:23:16.440 --> 1:23:18.000
Those were the rules
of this engagement.

1:23:18.040 --> 1:23:19.109
We were alone...

1:23:19.240 --> 1:23:21.151
In a public place.

1:23:21.640 --> 1:23:23.392
I can't be associated
with you there.

1:23:24.120 --> 1:23:25.917
At least one other person
knew who you were.

1:23:26.920 --> 1:23:28.069
Who was she, anyway?

1:23:28.800 --> 1:23:30.518
I never reveal
my clients. Ever.

1:23:30.600 --> 1:23:32.750
You just, uh, pry into
their personal lives,

1:23:32.880 --> 1:23:34.074
google for the truth.

1:23:34.320 --> 1:23:36.376
Yeah, I hear you lobbyists
ain't so good with the truth.

1:23:36.400 --> 1:23:37.753
Says the guy
with four identities,

1:23:37.880 --> 1:23:39.280
who sleeps with
strangers for money?

1:23:39.320 --> 1:23:41.560
I'm just surprised by what
a natural bullshitter you are.

1:23:41.600 --> 1:23:43.511
I grew up lying, Forde.

1:23:43.600 --> 1:23:45.272
Didn't want to. I had to.

1:23:45.880 --> 1:23:47.279
That's why I excel at it.

1:23:48.440 --> 1:23:50.158
It's a skill I would've
happily traded

1:23:50.280 --> 1:23:51.280
for a normal life.

1:23:53.600 --> 1:23:55.079
Normal's overrated.

1:24:37.480 --> 1:24:38.480
I'm sorry.

1:24:39.400 --> 1:24:40.435
I'm sorry.

1:24:43.280 --> 1:24:44.679
But I can't.

1:24:45.640 --> 1:24:46.834
What's wrong?

1:24:52.880 --> 1:24:54.632
- I'm sorry.
- Forget about tonight.

1:24:55.520 --> 1:24:57.238
Why? I do somethin'?

1:24:57.360 --> 1:24:59.032
No, it's, um...

1:25:00.680 --> 1:25:02.511
I'm not in
the right frame of mind.

1:25:04.240 --> 1:25:05.514
Here.

1:25:06.320 --> 1:25:08.834
- Easiest money you ever made.
- I didn't do anything.

1:25:09.680 --> 1:25:12.592
Well, you showed up,
I wasted your time, so, yeah.

1:25:13.160 --> 1:25:14.880
You know, we could just
sit and talk, and...

1:25:15.000 --> 1:25:16.480
Take the fucking money,
Forde!

1:25:22.920 --> 1:25:24.194
Get out, please.

1:25:30.680 --> 1:25:32.079
Suit yourself.

1:25:48.560 --> 1:25:49.754
Neumark.

1:25:50.120 --> 1:25:51.758
- Milner.
- Two hands here, come on.

1:25:51.880 --> 1:25:53.950
- Carlson...
- Wade Powell, Virginia.

1:25:54.080 --> 1:25:55.080
Hackman's come over too.

1:25:55.200 --> 1:25:57.270
We've lost Milner, Neumark,
Carlson, Hackman.

1:25:57.400 --> 1:25:59.256
Adamou's chief of staff said
he's softening his position.

1:25:59.280 --> 1:26:00.952
- Alex?
- I'll soften his fuckin'...

1:26:01.080 --> 1:26:02.433
Bill Sandford's on line 3.

1:26:02.560 --> 1:26:03.993
Closing Adamou
right the fuck now.

1:26:06.680 --> 1:26:07.715
She takes my own idea

1:26:07.800 --> 1:26:09.000
and goes up
against us with it.

1:26:09.080 --> 1:26:10.520
We did try
to warn you, Bill.

1:26:10.960 --> 1:26:13.474
Fifteen million.
From three million donors.

1:26:13.600 --> 1:26:14.749
In less than a quarter.

1:26:14.880 --> 1:26:17.110
You stop her,
you stop Heaton-Harris.

1:26:17.240 --> 1:26:18.593
We have to
make it personal now.

1:26:18.720 --> 1:26:19.835
She becomes the story.

1:26:20.080 --> 1:26:22.116
We can use our
media relationships, Bill,

1:26:22.280 --> 1:26:23.429
put her on the defensive.

1:26:23.560 --> 1:26:25.198
I don't just want her
on the defensive.

1:26:25.480 --> 1:26:27.675
I don't just want her
off the campaign.

1:26:27.960 --> 1:26:30.793
I want her to be the reason
that people think twice

1:26:30.920 --> 1:26:33.480
before taking on the guardians
of the Second Amendment.

1:26:34.160 --> 1:26:36.071
I want her career.

1:26:38.640 --> 1:26:40.437
Hey, Alex, it's me.
I just landed.

1:26:41.160 --> 1:26:43.400
Philadelphia was as good as
what we could have hoped for.

1:26:43.480 --> 1:26:45.710
- So how are we doing?
- That's four to go, people.

1:26:47.440 --> 1:26:48.839
You're kidding me.

1:26:50.960 --> 1:26:52.712
Wow, that's amazing.

1:26:52.800 --> 1:26:53.856
All right.

1:26:53.880 --> 1:26:55.320
We're joined now
by Esme Manucharian.

1:26:55.600 --> 1:26:57.079
Esme, thanks for joining us.

1:26:57.160 --> 1:26:58.957
Would you say that
the gun debate is now

1:26:59.080 --> 1:27:00.320
largely become
a women's issue?

1:27:00.360 --> 1:27:01.998
You need only
look at the numbers

1:27:02.120 --> 1:27:03.758
to see that gun safety
has become

1:27:03.840 --> 1:27:05.432
a deciding issue
for American women.

1:27:06.360 --> 1:27:08.032
If their representative
isn't listening,

1:27:08.160 --> 1:27:10.160
they'll go to the polls
and elect someone who will.

1:27:20.920 --> 1:27:22.114
What do you want?

1:27:22.840 --> 1:27:24.068
I got 15 million to blow.

1:27:25.520 --> 1:27:27.158
Lauren was going
through your letters.

1:27:27.640 --> 1:27:30.154
Between the death threats and
the hate mail, she found this.

1:27:31.680 --> 1:27:33.113
Pru Walsh
of The Sentinel is doing

1:27:33.200 --> 1:27:34.456
a feature on
the lobbying industry.

1:27:34.480 --> 1:27:35.549
That means you.

1:27:35.680 --> 1:27:37.920
Well, if she wants to meet me,
why did she send a letter?

1:27:38.120 --> 1:27:39.656
Because she doesn't really
want to meet you.

1:27:39.680 --> 1:27:40.976
She wants to say
she reached out to you

1:27:41.000 --> 1:27:42.520
for an interview,
but didn't hear back.

1:27:43.000 --> 1:27:44.000
It's a takedown.

1:27:44.120 --> 1:27:45.840
Well, the least we can do
is disappoint her.

1:27:47.360 --> 1:27:48.360
Set it up.

1:27:49.400 --> 1:27:50.799
I've canceled your 10:00 a.m.

1:27:50.880 --> 1:27:52.400
You're gonna see
our in-house attorney.

1:27:53.200 --> 1:27:54.480
I don't believe
you two have met.

1:27:56.400 --> 1:27:57.628
You know how
I feel about this.

1:27:57.720 --> 1:27:59.040
I was against you
ever hiring her.

1:27:59.400 --> 1:28:01.550
Because your job is not
winning lobbying fights,

1:28:01.880 --> 1:28:03.598
your job is
to stop us from getting...

1:28:06.840 --> 1:28:08.960
Quite independently of her
being utterly contemptible.

1:28:09.360 --> 1:28:10.793
What the hell
were you thinking?

1:28:10.880 --> 1:28:12.233
You know, whatever it was,

1:28:12.360 --> 1:28:14.157
I guess it seems
pretty stupid now.

1:28:15.040 --> 1:28:17.156
Liz, meet your protection.

1:28:28.600 --> 1:28:30.238
Daniel Posner, Head of Legal.

1:28:30.360 --> 1:28:32.271
Liz Sloane,
contemptible liability.

1:28:32.360 --> 1:28:33.554
And amateur lip-reader.

1:28:35.120 --> 1:28:37.111
Whose idea were
the glass walls? Seriously?

1:28:38.760 --> 1:28:40.557
Two TV slots tomorrow,

1:28:40.720 --> 1:28:44.076
then a radio thing, and
finally I'm done in Illinois.

1:28:44.560 --> 1:28:45.879
Where are you?

1:28:45.960 --> 1:28:47.336
Gold Stone,
waiting for them to hurry up

1:28:47.360 --> 1:28:48.429
and invent the food pill.

1:28:48.920 --> 1:28:50.478
That may take a while.

1:28:50.760 --> 1:28:53.320
And plotting to ensnare
our last four senators.

1:28:53.560 --> 1:28:56.074
Fifty-six down, four to go.
We're actually doing... Oh!

1:28:56.600 --> 1:28:58.830
- I'm sorry.
- I'm so sorry. My fault.

1:29:02.600 --> 1:29:04.272
- Thanks. Thank you.
- Here you go.

1:29:05.040 --> 1:29:06.040
Okay.

1:29:08.440 --> 1:29:09.714
Sorry about that.

1:29:09.800 --> 1:29:11.916
Remember that first day when
I asked how do we win,

1:29:12.040 --> 1:29:13.758
and you said
"Realistically, we don't"?

1:29:14.640 --> 1:29:16.437
I stand by every word of that.

1:29:16.760 --> 1:29:17.829
Excuse me?

1:29:18.240 --> 1:29:19.896
So you're going to downplay
the 15 million?

1:29:19.920 --> 1:29:21.056
Yeah, 'cause
we can't sound like

1:29:21.080 --> 1:29:23.275
we're bragging about
how much we're pulling in.

1:29:24.600 --> 1:29:27.160
Senators link donations
to voting intention,

1:29:27.280 --> 1:29:28.872
we can't say anything
that might stop...

1:29:28.960 --> 1:29:30.313
You wanna take this, bitch?

1:29:31.960 --> 1:29:32.960
Huh?

1:29:34.320 --> 1:29:35.720
Esme, you're still there?

1:29:35.840 --> 1:29:37.034
Come on.

1:29:38.920 --> 1:29:40.069
Take it.

1:29:44.320 --> 1:29:45.480
Esme? What the hell was that?

1:29:46.120 --> 1:29:47.269
You been here before, right?

1:29:48.080 --> 1:29:49.080
Esme?

1:29:49.440 --> 1:29:50.714
Look at me!

1:29:51.440 --> 1:29:52.589
Esme?

1:29:53.120 --> 1:29:54.640
Except I'm gonna
do it right this time.

1:30:16.680 --> 1:30:17.976
I'm standing at the scene

1:30:18.000 --> 1:30:19.228
of last night's shooting.

1:30:19.320 --> 1:30:20.799
We understand
that the assailant

1:30:21.120 --> 1:30:23.953
was targeting a leading figure
in the gun control movement,

1:30:24.040 --> 1:30:26.349
and was then shot dead
by a civilian

1:30:26.560 --> 1:30:28.994
carrying a registered,
concealed firearm.

1:30:29.680 --> 1:30:32.399
The name of the vigilante
has yet to be revealed...

1:30:33.680 --> 1:30:35.875
George?

1:30:36.200 --> 1:30:37.519
You're watching the news?

1:30:38.000 --> 1:30:39.672
Yeah, whole bunch of
Christmases

1:30:39.800 --> 1:30:41.233
just came early
for Bill Sandford.

1:30:42.040 --> 1:30:45.157
I'm headed to the airport.
Get ready to spend some money.

1:30:46.360 --> 1:30:48.360
Police have confirmed his
identity as Frank McGill.

1:30:49.040 --> 1:30:52.510
McGill was a legal owner
of a registered weapon.

1:30:52.840 --> 1:30:54.876
Heaton-Harris wouldn't have
touched him.

1:30:55.480 --> 1:30:56.913
But it might
have made it harder

1:30:57.040 --> 1:30:58.359
for the other son of a bitch.

1:30:58.480 --> 1:31:01.438
What do we know about him?
Where'd he get his piece?

1:31:01.560 --> 1:31:03.596
Did he have an arsenal
stashed in his basement...

1:31:04.720 --> 1:31:05.869
For the Second Amendment,

1:31:06.000 --> 1:31:08.195
which guaranteed her right
to be protected

1:31:08.320 --> 1:31:09.673
from a sick individual.

1:31:09.760 --> 1:31:11.990
And most of all,
for Frank McGill.

1:31:12.080 --> 1:31:15.311
Model citizen,
vigilant, responsible,

1:31:15.400 --> 1:31:16.913
and his aim is true.

1:31:46.560 --> 1:31:47.913
How are you doing?

1:31:58.040 --> 1:31:59.268
You heading home?

1:32:02.280 --> 1:32:03.793
You make a round-trip
from D.C.

1:32:03.920 --> 1:32:05.273
to pin me
in a departure lounge?

1:32:06.920 --> 1:32:08.638
So you can
check me off your list?

1:32:12.280 --> 1:32:14.589
I betrayed your confidence.
I set you down this path.

1:32:16.120 --> 1:32:17.680
"Don't worry, Liz,
it's not your fault."

1:32:17.760 --> 1:32:19.113
Is that what you wanna hear?

1:32:20.240 --> 1:32:21.878
"How could you
possibly have known?"

1:32:23.680 --> 1:32:24.999
You're not gonna get it.

1:32:26.960 --> 1:32:28.279
He wanted to kill me.

1:32:36.480 --> 1:32:38.835
I didn't know
where the line was, Esme.

1:32:45.160 --> 1:32:47.958
I never, never know
where the line is.

1:32:57.320 --> 1:32:58.800
Obviously,
take all the time you want.

1:32:59.160 --> 1:33:00.195
And when you're ready,

1:33:00.320 --> 1:33:02.000
we'd love to have you
back on the campaign.

1:33:02.880 --> 1:33:04.108
Your own terms.

1:33:04.200 --> 1:33:05.800
No media, you can work
behind the scenes.

1:33:09.000 --> 1:33:10.479
If you don't want
to work with me,

1:33:12.680 --> 1:33:14.079
I'll resign from the campaign.

1:33:16.640 --> 1:33:17.993
If that's what you want.

1:33:18.720 --> 1:33:20.836
Is that your move
to get me back at my desk?

1:33:22.360 --> 1:33:23.759
You want me
in front of a camera

1:33:23.840 --> 1:33:25.159
to counter Frank McGill?

1:33:30.840 --> 1:33:34.355
It even crossed my mind
that this was all you.

1:33:36.000 --> 1:33:37.228
You just didn't account

1:33:37.360 --> 1:33:38.840
for an armed civilian
right behind me.

1:33:40.200 --> 1:33:41.200
Esme...

1:33:41.240 --> 1:33:42.753
I'll keep fighting, Elizabeth.

1:33:43.920 --> 1:33:45.353
Wherever I can
make a difference.

1:33:47.320 --> 1:33:50.232
But as far as possible
away from you.

1:33:54.360 --> 1:33:56.078
You crossed the line
when you stopped

1:33:56.200 --> 1:33:57.394
treating people with respect.

1:33:58.880 --> 1:34:00.160
You're smart enough
to know that.

1:34:01.880 --> 1:34:03.029
You just don't care.

1:34:08.880 --> 1:34:10.880
Thank you,
thank you. Welcome back.

1:34:11.080 --> 1:34:12.399
Our next guest this morning is

1:34:12.520 --> 1:34:13.696
the kind of guy
you'd want to have around

1:34:13.720 --> 1:34:15.551
when you're walking home
from work one night

1:34:15.760 --> 1:34:17.671
and some dude sticks
a gun in your face.

1:34:17.760 --> 1:34:19.016
After his military career,

1:34:19.040 --> 1:34:20.632
McGill worked
as a commercial pilot...

1:34:20.720 --> 1:34:22.576
Let's face it,
folks, the streets ain 't safe.

1:34:22.600 --> 1:34:24.318
And if it wasn't for
the courage, bravery,

1:34:24.400 --> 1:34:26.470
and damn fine aim
of our next guest,

1:34:27.720 --> 1:34:30.075
we'd be reflecting
on yet another tragedy.

1:34:30.440 --> 1:34:32.237
Ladies and gentlemen,
please welcome

1:34:32.360 --> 1:34:34.954
the man of the moment,
Frank McGill.

1:34:38.200 --> 1:34:41.670
So, Frank McGill,
all-American hero.

1:34:41.920 --> 1:34:43.512
Not at all.
An ordinary guy

1:34:43.600 --> 1:34:45.113
in the right place
at the right time.

1:34:45.280 --> 1:34:47.120
With
a 9 milli. under his belt.

1:34:47.440 --> 1:34:51.353
I'm curious. The person whose
life you saved once campaigned

1:34:51.440 --> 1:34:53.670
for a ban on concealed carry.

1:34:53.760 --> 1:34:55.273
How do you feel about that?

1:34:55.400 --> 1:34:57.436
I respectfully disagree
with those views.

1:34:57.560 --> 1:34:59.320
But the young lady is
entitled to her opinion

1:34:59.640 --> 1:35:01.360
and nobody should be
attacking her for that,

1:35:01.800 --> 1:35:03.153
much less holding her
at gunpoint.

1:35:04.120 --> 1:35:05.792
McGill's a gift from God.

1:35:07.440 --> 1:35:08.953
But it won't last forever.

1:35:09.960 --> 1:35:11.518
We're looking to parlay that

1:35:11.640 --> 1:35:13.278
into a closer examination
of Sloane.

1:35:13.520 --> 1:35:15.476
I'm thinking of
a Congressional hearing

1:35:15.600 --> 1:35:19.070
into her unorthodox
lobbying practices.

1:35:20.440 --> 1:35:23.955
I'm sure we can find a senator
who may be open to the idea.

1:35:24.480 --> 1:35:26.056
You want to talk trash
about her in the press,

1:35:26.080 --> 1:35:27.080
that's one thing.

1:35:27.120 --> 1:35:28.872
A Congressional hearing
requires

1:35:28.960 --> 1:35:31.599
a convincing allegation
of impropriety.

1:35:31.680 --> 1:35:34.194
I'd give my left nut to drag
her rep through the dirt,

1:35:34.320 --> 1:35:35.594
but you're not gonna get it.

1:35:35.680 --> 1:35:37.557
She's a CYA specialist.

1:35:38.600 --> 1:35:40.989
I've never met
anyone so pedantic...

1:35:41.120 --> 1:35:42.473
Start an inquisition.

1:35:44.000 --> 1:35:46.594
Let's see how well-covered
her ass really is.

1:35:49.560 --> 1:35:50.675
Hi.

1:35:52.200 --> 1:35:54.031
Pru Walsh. Thanks so much
for coming over.

1:35:54.280 --> 1:35:56.080
This is Mike Gordon
from our legal department.

1:35:56.520 --> 1:35:57.714
Daniel Posner from ours.

1:35:58.040 --> 1:36:00.110
Miss Sloane,
you're at the forefront

1:36:00.200 --> 1:36:02.395
of an industry
with a terrible reputation.

1:36:02.680 --> 1:36:03.840
Do you think that's deserved?

1:36:05.800 --> 1:36:07.336
The only reason this bill
wasn't passed decades ago

1:36:07.360 --> 1:36:09.120
is because of the power
of special interests.

1:36:09.240 --> 1:36:10.673
When a lobbyist
raises finance...

1:36:11.200 --> 1:36:12.536
We haven't heard
from Esme Manucharian

1:36:12.560 --> 1:36:14.915
since the attack.
Are you in contact with her?

1:36:16.040 --> 1:36:17.439
That's a private matter.

1:36:17.680 --> 1:36:19.136
I think what's important
to remember...

1:36:19.160 --> 1:36:20.639
So have you
talked to her at all?

1:36:21.080 --> 1:36:23.355
What is important to remember
here is that Frank McGill

1:36:23.640 --> 1:36:25.278
is exactly
the kind of law-abiding,

1:36:25.680 --> 1:36:27.079
responsible gun owner

1:36:27.200 --> 1:36:29.191
whose rights the
Heaton-Harris Bill protects.

1:36:29.320 --> 1:36:30.960
Do you feel any guilt
about what happened?

1:36:31.320 --> 1:36:32.514
Why would I feel guilt?

1:36:32.880 --> 1:36:34.916
You made Esme the face
of your campaign.

1:36:35.200 --> 1:36:36.599
You thrust her
into the limelight

1:36:36.680 --> 1:36:37.795
that night on the debate.

1:36:37.880 --> 1:36:39.536
- I'm not talking about this.
- You don't have to.

1:36:39.560 --> 1:36:40.576
Did she know
that you were going to

1:36:40.600 --> 1:36:42.556
out her on national TV?
Did she agree to that?

1:36:42.840 --> 1:36:45.229
Why not report that
the majority of gun owners

1:36:45.400 --> 1:36:47.118
favor more extensive
background checks?

1:36:47.200 --> 1:36:48.536
She probably went
her entire career

1:36:48.560 --> 1:36:49.736
trying to keep that
a carefully guarded secret.

1:36:49.760 --> 1:36:50.936
That the gun lobby's
fear-mongering rhetoric

1:36:50.960 --> 1:36:53.200
is trying to paint Heaton-Harris
into something it's not.

1:36:53.720 --> 1:36:55.280
Do you think
that your little revelation

1:36:55.680 --> 1:36:57.272
is what made her a target?

1:36:57.400 --> 1:36:58.435
It's clear Miss Sloane

1:36:58.560 --> 1:36:59.696
doesn't wish to discuss
Ms. Manucharian.

1:36:59.720 --> 1:37:00.800
What's really clear is that

1:37:00.880 --> 1:37:02.080
your article's
already written.

1:37:02.280 --> 1:37:03.376
Don't respond to that.

1:37:03.400 --> 1:37:04.920
That's purely speculative
on your part.

1:37:05.080 --> 1:37:06.957
- Who's controlling you?
- Let's not do this.

1:37:07.080 --> 1:37:08.840
Look, the fact is,
you have no way of knowing

1:37:08.920 --> 1:37:10.120
what Ms. Walsh
intends to do...

1:37:10.240 --> 1:37:11.536
The fact is that
you have no interest

1:37:11.560 --> 1:37:12.834
in what Miss Sloane
has to say.

1:37:13.200 --> 1:37:15.360
- And how would you know that?
- Your Dictaphone's off.

1:37:20.760 --> 1:37:22.079
Takedown.

1:37:22.440 --> 1:37:23.800
It could've been worse.

1:37:23.920 --> 1:37:25.990
I've got four
factual errors so far.

1:37:26.560 --> 1:37:27.788
This is not good, Liz.

1:37:28.080 --> 1:37:29.399
Dump it in the recycling.

1:37:29.480 --> 1:37:30.680
They'll make
pencils out of it.

1:37:31.240 --> 1:37:32.480
Maybe one will
find its way into

1:37:32.520 --> 1:37:34.272
the hands of a reporter
with some integrity.

1:37:34.600 --> 1:37:35.749
It will go away.

1:37:38.280 --> 1:37:39.474
Okay, thank you.

1:37:41.120 --> 1:37:42.120
Bye.

1:37:45.120 --> 1:37:47.509
Funny how all these senators
are suddenly very busy.

1:37:49.800 --> 1:37:51.438
We all know why that is.

1:37:55.560 --> 1:37:57.073
Okay, so it's not great.

1:37:58.160 --> 1:38:00.071
The 15 million
helped us get this far,

1:38:00.160 --> 1:38:01.920
but it doesn't last long
when you're fighting

1:38:02.000 --> 1:38:03.228
the richest group on the Hill.

1:38:03.520 --> 1:38:04.589
Let's get to the point.

1:38:04.680 --> 1:38:06.136
How does it shake out
when it comes to the vote?

1:38:06.160 --> 1:38:08.993
We'd run them close.
But by latest projections,

1:38:09.640 --> 1:38:11.790
we'll be between four
to seven votes short.

1:38:13.360 --> 1:38:14.880
There's nothing more
we can do tonight.

1:38:16.160 --> 1:38:17.388
Liz, we don't have to leave.

1:38:17.800 --> 1:38:19.153
The West Coast is still awake.

1:38:19.480 --> 1:38:20.616
We can
connect with Oregon.

1:38:20.640 --> 1:38:21.993
If we close those
goddamn loggers,

1:38:22.120 --> 1:38:23.496
we could get it
to five votes tonight.

1:38:23.520 --> 1:38:25.511
Go home
and get some rest, guys.

1:38:25.640 --> 1:38:26.800
You've done enough for today.

1:38:27.480 --> 1:38:29.136
I'll take to the streets
and rip down those

1:38:29.160 --> 1:38:31.720
fucking Frank McGill posters
one at a time if I have to.

1:38:32.160 --> 1:38:33.991
Go home,
sharpen your knives.

1:38:34.440 --> 1:38:35.759
It'll still be on tomorrow.

1:39:09.240 --> 1:39:10.639
So we keep on fighting.

1:39:11.360 --> 1:39:12.873
That's all we can do.

1:39:13.680 --> 1:39:15.159
As my ex-wife used to say.

1:39:20.080 --> 1:39:21.480
I met you running
from a fundraiser.

1:39:23.200 --> 1:39:24.440
You could be done
with all this.

1:39:25.920 --> 1:39:27.194
Why don't you quit?

1:39:31.760 --> 1:39:33.193
And do what?

1:39:48.200 --> 1:39:49.519
Good night.

1:40:25.120 --> 1:40:26.269
Hello?

1:40:27.920 --> 1:40:29.353
I'm surprised you picked up.

1:40:31.960 --> 1:40:33.473
I'm sorry, you have
the wrong number.

1:41:50.200 --> 1:41:52.760
She'd ply Congressmen
with benefits,

1:41:53.400 --> 1:41:56.676
free meals, tickets to events,
golfing weekends.

1:41:56.760 --> 1:41:59.194
All paid for by our clients,
via the firm.

1:41:59.280 --> 1:42:00.759
Well, that right there's
enough.

1:42:00.840 --> 1:42:02.592
She'd make a point
of invoicing them,

1:42:02.720 --> 1:42:04.517
though they were never
expected to pay.

1:42:05.040 --> 1:42:06.896
The debt shows as an asset
on our balance sheet.

1:42:06.920 --> 1:42:08.797
We can call it in
any time we want.

1:42:08.880 --> 1:42:10.916
You were her
right hand for two years.

1:42:12.880 --> 1:42:15.030
There's got to be something.

1:42:17.520 --> 1:42:18.953
Why's nobody
on her files?

1:42:19.040 --> 1:42:21.376
There were a ton of us,
but the others got pulled out.

1:42:21.400 --> 1:42:23.136
It's not like we're in danger
of finding anything.

1:42:23.160 --> 1:42:24.354
Well, how far d'you get?

1:42:24.440 --> 1:42:25.998
We worked backwards
from her last deal

1:42:26.080 --> 1:42:27.229
before she jumped ship.

1:42:27.320 --> 1:42:28.536
They said it'd
be better if we can

1:42:28.560 --> 1:42:29.720
nail her on something recent.

1:42:29.760 --> 1:42:31.955
- Which was?
- Shmallow Cakes.

1:42:32.080 --> 1:42:33.115
Some tax thing.

1:42:33.200 --> 1:42:35.111
She left halfway through.

1:42:35.200 --> 1:42:36.792
I thought it was
the palm oil thing.

1:42:36.920 --> 1:42:37.955
Palm oil?

1:42:38.040 --> 1:42:39.268
Nutella Tax.

1:42:40.680 --> 1:42:41.829
Hold on.

1:42:43.120 --> 1:42:44.838
The Indonesians?

1:42:44.920 --> 1:42:46.400
I don't
remember seeing that.

1:42:54.200 --> 1:42:55.394
What are you looking for?

1:42:59.200 --> 1:43:00.428
Mr. Dupont,

1:43:01.120 --> 1:43:02.758
she's in breach of
Senate Ethics rules.

1:43:03.480 --> 1:43:04.549
We can prove it.

1:43:24.480 --> 1:43:27.119
Things not looking so good
for you this cycle, Ron.

1:43:29.480 --> 1:43:32.438
You ask me, you're gonna need
a lot more paid media.

1:43:32.960 --> 1:43:34.040
I didn't ask you.

1:43:34.080 --> 1:43:38.949
Now, who might just be able to
fund those coveted TV spots?

1:43:39.320 --> 1:43:41.038
I'm committed
to Heaton-Harris,

1:43:41.280 --> 1:43:42.998
I can't vote for it
with one hand

1:43:43.400 --> 1:43:44.879
and choke it with the other.

1:43:44.960 --> 1:43:46.951
Under cover of impartiality,
sure you can.

1:43:47.520 --> 1:43:50.512
You've been a vocal critic
of lobbyists in the past.

1:43:50.720 --> 1:43:53.553
You'll lead an inquiry
into Sloane's affairs

1:43:53.640 --> 1:43:55.915
in response to
growing media pressure

1:43:56.160 --> 1:43:58.310
regarding her
litany of misdeeds.

1:43:58.920 --> 1:44:03.311
The cost of hearings
is paid from the public purse.

1:44:04.080 --> 1:44:06.389
Ron, our clients
have identified you

1:44:06.480 --> 1:44:08.596
as the man to pull this off.

1:44:08.720 --> 1:44:09.755
If you decline,

1:44:09.840 --> 1:44:11.273
I can't stop them from

1:44:11.360 --> 1:44:13.715
blitzing you
with negative finance.

1:44:14.480 --> 1:44:17.631
They won't stop
until they annihilate you.

1:44:19.040 --> 1:44:21.600
You know the root
of the word "annihilate"?

1:44:22.680 --> 1:44:23.795
It's Latin.

1:44:25.320 --> 1:44:27.470
It means, "reduce to nothing."

1:44:29.240 --> 1:44:31.470
That's what they're
going to do to you, Ron.

1:44:31.560 --> 1:44:34.632
So, what? I'll be taking
a wedge from Bill Sandford

1:44:35.520 --> 1:44:36.748
and leading the attack

1:44:36.840 --> 1:44:39.070
on Heaton-Harris'
most visible advocate?

1:44:39.160 --> 1:44:41.276
A 6th grader could
connect the dots.

1:44:41.360 --> 1:44:44.909
We can create a structure
to obfuscate the source.

1:44:45.400 --> 1:44:46.958
Your big wedge will arrive

1:44:47.040 --> 1:44:50.077
courtesy of eight to 12 smaller entities

1:44:50.160 --> 1:44:52.116
with no affiliation to guns.

1:44:55.600 --> 1:44:56.999
How big a wedge we talking?

1:44:59.880 --> 1:45:01.233
Big enough

1:45:02.080 --> 1:45:03.593
to be the difference between

1:45:03.680 --> 1:45:05.398
the continuation
of your duties

1:45:05.480 --> 1:45:07.152
as a United States Senator

1:45:07.840 --> 1:45:10.354
and the reduction
of your career to nothing.

1:45:26.280 --> 1:45:27.474
This is every hit since

1:45:27.560 --> 1:45:29.915
the original Pru Walsh
hack-job two weeks ago.

1:45:30.880 --> 1:45:32.279
My personal favorite
is the one

1:45:32.360 --> 1:45:33.429
about how you toppled

1:45:33.520 --> 1:45:34.896
the head of the High School
Student Council

1:45:34.920 --> 1:45:36.831
with a fabricated
plagiarism scandal.

1:45:37.640 --> 1:45:39.278
I'm assuming
that's not libelous

1:45:39.360 --> 1:45:40.793
'cause I can totally see it.

1:45:41.160 --> 1:45:42.718
That witch was insufferable.

1:45:43.760 --> 1:45:45.360
I'm taking you
off the campaign.

1:45:45.600 --> 1:45:46.600
What?

1:45:47.680 --> 1:45:49.033
Not you, her.

1:45:50.200 --> 1:45:51.235
I'll be outside.

1:45:52.760 --> 1:45:54.193
What are you talking about?

1:45:54.280 --> 1:45:55.474
Heaton-Harris gets colder

1:45:55.560 --> 1:45:56.960
every day you're
associated with it.

1:45:57.960 --> 1:45:59.200
Sperling's got
the hots for you.

1:45:59.760 --> 1:46:01.478
I haven't even met him,
this is a setup.

1:46:02.000 --> 1:46:03.319
If they're orchestrating it,

1:46:03.400 --> 1:46:05.080
it's because they want me
off the campaign.

1:46:07.280 --> 1:46:09.040
Right now, you're lawyering up
for a hearing.

1:46:13.720 --> 1:46:15.136
Regarding your representation

1:46:15.160 --> 1:46:16.354
of the Indonesian government.

1:46:16.440 --> 1:46:17.714
Dan, are you busy?

1:46:17.800 --> 1:46:19.000
Senator Allen Jacobs,

1:46:19.360 --> 1:46:22.636
the sponsor of the bill
you dubbed the Nutella Tax,

1:46:24.920 --> 1:46:26.990
was flown to Indonesia
first-class with his family,

1:46:27.200 --> 1:46:29.430
and put up at a 5-star hotel.

1:46:30.160 --> 1:46:34.119
Our audit puts the cost
of this trip at over $30,000.

1:46:34.480 --> 1:46:36.152
Shortly after his return,

1:46:36.240 --> 1:46:38.913
the bill was pulled
from consideration.

1:46:40.760 --> 1:46:42.796
Now, why do you suppose
this happened?

1:46:42.880 --> 1:46:45.678
I understand the trip was
for educational purposes.

1:46:45.760 --> 1:46:48.354
I can surmise that
he learned how his bill

1:46:48.440 --> 1:46:49.953
would have strangled
a key industry,

1:46:50.040 --> 1:46:51.553
and confined thousands

1:46:51.640 --> 1:46:54.279
of impoverished farmers
to destitution.

1:46:54.360 --> 1:46:56.078
From his private beach?

1:46:57.160 --> 1:47:00.470
No. The truth is,
your client funded this trip

1:47:00.600 --> 1:47:03.797
as an inducement for the
senator to withdraw his bill.

1:47:04.160 --> 1:47:05.513
- Isn't that right?
- Not at all.

1:47:05.600 --> 1:47:07.318
My client was
the Indonesian Government.

1:47:07.440 --> 1:47:08.634
The trip was sponsored

1:47:08.720 --> 1:47:10.392
by the Institute of
Environmental Studies,

1:47:10.480 --> 1:47:13.552
a 501 C-3
non-profit organization.

1:47:13.640 --> 1:47:14.755
Travel was pre-approved

1:47:14.840 --> 1:47:16.671
by the Senate Ethics
Committee.

1:47:16.760 --> 1:47:19.558
Has your client ever
donated to this non-profit?

1:47:20.000 --> 1:47:21.228
I wouldn't know that.

1:47:21.320 --> 1:47:22.958
I'm not privy
to their list of donors.

1:47:23.080 --> 1:47:26.072
Nor had I any role
in arranging funding for this.

1:47:26.800 --> 1:47:28.313
- No role?
- Mmm.

1:47:29.040 --> 1:47:31.349
Of course,
you couldn't have any role

1:47:31.920 --> 1:47:34.912
because the Senate Ethics
rules prevent lobbyists

1:47:35.240 --> 1:47:38.073
from arranging overseas travel
for members of Congress.

1:47:38.160 --> 1:47:39.388
Indeed.

1:47:43.040 --> 1:47:44.268
Do you know what this is?

1:47:46.400 --> 1:47:47.600
Perhaps we can get you a copy.

1:47:55.560 --> 1:47:56.879
Are you familiar
with that form?

1:47:58.320 --> 1:48:00.197
Yes. It's a Private Sponsor
Certification Form.

1:48:00.280 --> 1:48:01.918
It's a copy of the same

1:48:02.000 --> 1:48:03.718
Private Sponsor
Certification Form

1:48:03.800 --> 1:48:06.075
that was submitted
to the Senate Ethics Committee

1:48:06.160 --> 1:48:08.879
to pre-authorize
Senator Jacobs' travel

1:48:09.000 --> 1:48:10.149
to Indonesia.

1:48:10.680 --> 1:48:13.274
Look at the handwriting
on that form, Miss Sloane.

1:48:15.160 --> 1:48:16.878
Do you recognize
that handwriting?

1:48:17.720 --> 1:48:18.755
Yes, I do.

1:48:18.840 --> 1:48:20.120
Is it your handwriting?

1:48:23.120 --> 1:48:24.269
It is.

1:48:26.440 --> 1:48:28.078
Well, it seems
we have a problem.

1:48:28.840 --> 1:48:30.956
Even though
the form was signed

1:48:31.040 --> 1:48:32.189
and filed by the non-profit,

1:48:32.280 --> 1:48:33.998
you were the one
who filled it out.

1:48:34.560 --> 1:48:36.198
This is prima facie evidence

1:48:36.320 --> 1:48:38.311
that you were involved
in arranging

1:48:38.400 --> 1:48:40.391
overseas travel for
a member of Congress.

1:48:41.160 --> 1:48:44.994
Constituting a clear breach
of Senate Ethics rules.

1:48:45.240 --> 1:48:46.639
Is that your trump card?

1:48:48.280 --> 1:48:49.474
You drag me in here,

1:48:49.560 --> 1:48:51.710
wedge an endoscope
up my posterior,

1:48:52.040 --> 1:48:54.554
and all this time,
the only incriminating item

1:48:54.640 --> 1:48:57.279
you have in your possession
is a filing snafu?

1:48:57.360 --> 1:48:59.237
How about surveillance,
Miss Sloane?

1:48:59.440 --> 1:49:02.557
Mr. Rodolfo Schmidt
has stated in deposition

1:49:03.040 --> 1:49:05.235
that you intended
to use methods

1:49:05.320 --> 1:49:07.038
such as bugging and tapping

1:49:07.120 --> 1:49:10.351
to entrap Senator
Hank Badgley. Is this true?

1:49:10.480 --> 1:49:13.870
I did, for a brief moment,
intend to use such methods.

1:49:13.960 --> 1:49:15.996
But that intention
was never acted upon.

1:49:16.080 --> 1:49:17.229
And why was that?

1:49:17.360 --> 1:49:19.271
Mr. Schmidt
expressly forbade it,

1:49:19.360 --> 1:49:21.316
as he no doubt told you
in his deposition.

1:49:21.400 --> 1:49:22.536
But you were clearly
comfortable

1:49:22.560 --> 1:49:23.595
with these methods.

1:49:24.040 --> 1:49:27.316
Did you employ the tactics
of espionage

1:49:27.400 --> 1:49:29.595
regularly throughout
your lobbying career?

1:49:29.680 --> 1:49:30.954
No, I did not.

1:49:31.040 --> 1:49:32.136
Then let me ask you this.

1:49:32.160 --> 1:49:34.071
Have you ever authorized,
ordered,

1:49:34.160 --> 1:49:35.752
or otherwise brought about

1:49:35.880 --> 1:49:38.917
any kind of unlawful
surveillance on any person?

1:49:39.960 --> 1:49:41.951
Let me remind you that perjury

1:49:42.040 --> 1:49:43.758
before Congress
is a felony, which...

1:49:43.840 --> 1:49:44.875
The answer is no.

1:49:46.400 --> 1:49:49.597
I have never authorized
illegal surveillance.

1:49:53.160 --> 1:49:55.151
This concludes my questioning
of the witness.

1:49:55.240 --> 1:49:56.559
Thank you, Miss Sloane.

1:50:05.720 --> 1:50:07.199
We have one further witness.

1:50:08.920 --> 1:50:10.751
Either you just
perjured yourself,

1:50:10.840 --> 1:50:12.671
or you're not
so sleazy after all.

1:50:13.440 --> 1:50:15.280
The Committee
calls Mr. Robert Forde.

1:50:16.120 --> 1:50:17.439
I wouldn't count on that.

1:50:19.400 --> 1:50:20.628
Mr. Chairman, I don't recall

1:50:20.720 --> 1:50:22.200
being notified
of your intention to...

1:50:22.240 --> 1:50:23.275
We were only recently

1:50:23.360 --> 1:50:24.696
able to locate
the witness, Mr. Posner.

1:50:24.720 --> 1:50:25.755
Let it play.

1:50:26.520 --> 1:50:28.192
A moment
with my client, please?

1:50:29.040 --> 1:50:30.871
What is this?
Who's Robert Forde?

1:50:32.160 --> 1:50:33.639
Look, I can make
a public appeal...

1:50:33.720 --> 1:50:34.755
Let it play, damn it.

1:50:34.840 --> 1:50:36.920
They're going to get it
out there one way or another.

1:50:50.440 --> 1:50:52.715
Mr. Forde,
please raise your right hand.

1:50:54.040 --> 1:50:56.076
Do you solemnly swear
that you will tell the truth,

1:50:56.160 --> 1:50:58.071
the whole truth,
and nothing but the truth,

1:50:58.440 --> 1:51:00.192
under pains and penalties
of perjury?

1:51:00.520 --> 1:51:02.078
- I swear.
- Please sit.

1:51:07.880 --> 1:51:10.314
Mr. Forde,
could you please describe

1:51:10.400 --> 1:51:11.992
the nature of your work?

1:51:14.480 --> 1:51:15.879
I got many jobs.

1:51:18.040 --> 1:51:21.077
What would you say earns you
the most income at present?

1:51:22.920 --> 1:51:24.000
I work as an escort in D.C.

1:51:29.760 --> 1:51:31.432
You sleep
with women for money?

1:51:32.080 --> 1:51:33.479
I meet the clients' needs.

1:51:34.480 --> 1:51:35.674
Whatever they may be.

1:51:36.720 --> 1:51:39.359
Sometimes, the client don't
even know what they need.

1:51:40.240 --> 1:51:42.071
Part of my job's
to figure that out.

1:51:42.160 --> 1:51:43.798
But, sometimes,
your job entails

1:51:44.440 --> 1:51:46.237
having intercourse
for payment?

1:51:47.920 --> 1:51:49.194
Yes, sir.

1:51:49.920 --> 1:51:52.036
Have you ever met
Elizabeth Sloane?

1:51:52.120 --> 1:51:53.656
Mr. Chairman, the Senate
has no business

1:51:53.680 --> 1:51:55.560
prying into the personal
affairs of Miss Sloane.

1:51:55.640 --> 1:51:57.000
Solicitation
is a criminal offense.

1:51:57.040 --> 1:51:59.395
It's well within the remit
of this hearing

1:51:59.480 --> 1:52:00.799
to establish
whether Miss Sloane

1:52:00.880 --> 1:52:01.949
has broken any laws.

1:52:02.800 --> 1:52:03.835
Mr. Forde.

1:52:04.440 --> 1:52:06.715
Have you ever met Miss Sloane?

1:52:08.360 --> 1:52:09.395
Yep.

1:52:09.840 --> 1:52:11.398
Could you
identify her, please?

1:52:13.720 --> 1:52:14.869
Sittin' right there.

1:52:15.640 --> 1:52:18.029
What was the nature
of your relationship?

1:52:21.000 --> 1:52:23.150
I was attendin'
a function with a client.

1:52:24.000 --> 1:52:26.000
I tried to introduce myself,
but she bucked me off.

1:52:28.480 --> 1:52:29.833
Mr. Forde, have you ever

1:52:29.920 --> 1:52:31.320
entertained Miss Sloane
as a client?

1:52:36.440 --> 1:52:37.509
No, sir.

1:52:39.280 --> 1:52:41.157
I can produce sworn statements

1:52:41.240 --> 1:52:43.674
from two employees
of the Carver Hotel,

1:52:43.760 --> 1:52:46.672
to the effect that they saw
Miss Sloane in the lobby

1:52:47.120 --> 1:52:48.917
on the same day
that you, Mr. Forde,

1:52:49.000 --> 1:52:50.513
held a reservation there.

1:52:50.960 --> 1:52:52.029
I ask again.

1:52:52.160 --> 1:52:56.073
Did you entertain Miss Sloane
in any capacity, for profit?

1:52:56.280 --> 1:52:57.508
No, sir. I did not.

1:53:01.080 --> 1:53:02.752
Thank you,
Mr. Forde.

1:53:03.560 --> 1:53:04.879
You're dismissed.

1:53:10.480 --> 1:53:12.277
These proceedings
will conclude tomorrow,

1:53:13.280 --> 1:53:16.955
when Miss Sloane is referred
to the Senate Ethics Committee

1:53:17.040 --> 1:53:18.439
for their judgment.

1:53:29.040 --> 1:53:31.315
I can't believe those fuckers
dragged that guy...

1:53:31.400 --> 1:53:32.549
Ross?

1:53:36.440 --> 1:53:37.800
How's our old friend
Heaton-Harris?

1:53:40.440 --> 1:53:42.829
Comatose. The whole
issue's gone cold.

1:53:44.800 --> 1:53:46.313
That is what they wanted.

1:53:47.600 --> 1:53:49.680
We all know what
it would take to revive it.

1:53:50.760 --> 1:53:52.910
Seriously, an earthquake.

1:53:55.400 --> 1:53:57.231
We got closer than
we had any right to.

1:54:06.120 --> 1:54:07.599
We'll all be there tomorrow.

1:54:41.880 --> 1:54:43.336
Excuse me,
Miss Sloane, over here.

1:54:43.360 --> 1:54:44.475
May I have a comment?

1:55:02.640 --> 1:55:03.709
Good morning.

1:55:09.920 --> 1:55:12.309
Before referring
the witness's testimony

1:55:12.400 --> 1:55:14.436
to the Office
of Congressional Ethics,

1:55:14.520 --> 1:55:16.158
she is entitled
to make a statement.

1:55:19.160 --> 1:55:22.436
Miss Sloane, is there
something you'd like to say?

1:55:35.680 --> 1:55:37.961
Mr. Chairman, my client does
not wish to make a statement.

1:55:39.840 --> 1:55:40.875
Very well.

1:55:40.960 --> 1:55:42.473
I will now read the referral

1:55:42.560 --> 1:55:44.312
to the office of
Congressional Ethics...

1:55:44.400 --> 1:55:46.197
There is something
I'd like to say, Senator.

1:56:15.720 --> 1:56:18.553
I have been censured by
the press and by this hearing

1:56:19.400 --> 1:56:20.799
as a parasite

1:56:21.760 --> 1:56:23.398
on American democracy.

1:56:24.640 --> 1:56:27.200
It's insinuated
that I led the fight

1:56:28.240 --> 1:56:32.438
for increased gun regulation
in the interest of my career.

1:56:35.080 --> 1:56:37.196
Sometimes we act,
not for ourselves,

1:56:39.600 --> 1:56:41.955
but because we believe
plainly and simply

1:56:42.080 --> 1:56:43.433
it is the right thing to do.

1:56:43.600 --> 1:56:46.068
Miss Sloane, is this pertinent
to the discussions we...

1:56:46.160 --> 1:56:49.277
I understand I have the right
to say what I wish, Senator.

1:56:50.440 --> 1:56:51.440
Proceed.

1:56:53.600 --> 1:56:55.192
I believe
the Heaton-Harris Bill

1:56:55.320 --> 1:56:56.594
is the right thing to do.

1:56:59.600 --> 1:57:00.874
But I also recognize

1:57:01.440 --> 1:57:05.479
that this wasn't
what motivated me.

1:57:08.160 --> 1:57:10.515
When I was offered a position
on the campaign,

1:57:10.600 --> 1:57:12.591
I was in thrall
to the challenge.

1:57:15.040 --> 1:57:19.830
My decision to accept
was based on my desire to win.

1:57:23.640 --> 1:57:25.631
And to win bigger
than I ever had before.

1:57:29.880 --> 1:57:32.758
It's clear that my behavior
has fallen well short

1:57:34.320 --> 1:57:37.471
of acceptable
ethical standards.

1:57:39.320 --> 1:57:43.359
I've crossed lines
with devastating consequences

1:57:44.560 --> 1:57:46.391
in the service
of my obsession.

1:57:48.840 --> 1:57:50.910
I've betrayed the people
closest to me.

1:57:54.360 --> 1:57:55.873
I've endangered lives.

1:57:58.920 --> 1:58:00.512
I deserve censure for this

1:58:01.560 --> 1:58:04.677
far more than for
any filing irregularity.

1:58:07.720 --> 1:58:10.154
When they consider
the Heaton-Harris Bill, I wish

1:58:11.520 --> 1:58:13.192
that each member of Congress

1:58:13.320 --> 1:58:15.595
would follow the example set,
not by me,

1:58:17.040 --> 1:58:19.873
but by the group of people
that sit behind me.

1:58:21.720 --> 1:58:24.075
Who have made great sacrifices

1:58:24.680 --> 1:58:28.195
in the name of doing
what they believe is right.

1:58:29.680 --> 1:58:33.958
I wish that those members
would use their votes,

1:58:34.040 --> 1:58:37.953
not in the interest of
their political advancement,

1:58:38.760 --> 1:58:43.197
but for what they believe
is right for their country.

1:58:45.400 --> 1:58:46.958
But I know my wishes
are wasted.

1:58:48.440 --> 1:58:50.112
And that this will
never happen.

1:58:51.400 --> 1:58:54.870
Because our system is rotten.

1:58:57.400 --> 1:58:59.675
It doesn't reward
honest politicians,

1:58:59.760 --> 1:59:01.034
who vote with
their conscience.

1:59:02.880 --> 1:59:04.233
It rewards

1:59:05.320 --> 1:59:06.469
rats

1:59:07.560 --> 1:59:09.357
who are willing to
sell out their country

1:59:09.440 --> 1:59:10.760
to keep their noses
in the trough.

1:59:12.720 --> 1:59:14.278
Make no mistake.

1:59:15.240 --> 1:59:18.357
These rats are
the real parasites

1:59:19.400 --> 1:59:20.992
on American democracy.

1:59:34.240 --> 1:59:36.913
I anticipated if we had
sufficient success

1:59:37.000 --> 1:59:38.991
in lobbying for
the Heaton-Harris Bill,

1:59:39.080 --> 1:59:40.479
there may be

1:59:41.680 --> 1:59:43.591
an assault
against me personally,

1:59:45.280 --> 1:59:49.512
to stall our momentum
and to damage our credibility.

1:59:52.760 --> 1:59:54.273
Lobbying is about foresight.

1:59:56.120 --> 1:59:58.111
About anticipating
your opponent's moves

2:00:00.280 --> 2:00:01.508
and devising counter-measures.

2:00:02.320 --> 2:00:03.833
I'd like to discuss my future.

2:00:04.800 --> 2:00:06.472
This is hardly
the time, cookie.

2:00:07.280 --> 2:00:10.636
The winner plots one step
ahead of the opposition,

2:00:12.120 --> 2:00:15.829
and plays a trump card
just after they play theirs.

2:00:16.720 --> 2:00:18.073
Actually, it is the time.

2:00:18.960 --> 2:00:20.240
It's about making sure

2:00:20.280 --> 2:00:21.508
you surprise them.

2:00:22.640 --> 2:00:24.039
The fuck is this?

2:00:24.800 --> 2:00:26.199
And that they don't
surprise you.

2:00:27.000 --> 2:00:28.399
My resignation.

2:00:28.960 --> 2:00:30.632
Academia's more my scene.

2:00:35.640 --> 2:00:38.632
When I left Cole, Kravitz,
and Waterman,

2:00:39.840 --> 2:00:43.196
I retained an operative
of mine in their ranks.

2:00:44.880 --> 2:00:46.233
All right, Jane.

2:00:46.320 --> 2:00:47.616
Contact Rodolfo Schmidt
and tell him

2:00:47.640 --> 2:00:49.016
there is a total
of six coming over.

2:00:49.040 --> 2:00:50.075
Who says I'm coming?

2:00:51.000 --> 2:00:52.280
A plan was hatched to

2:00:52.320 --> 2:00:53.480
bankroll a trumped-up hearing

2:00:54.040 --> 2:00:55.837
at the behest
of the gun lobby.

2:00:55.920 --> 2:00:57.433
There's got to be something.

2:00:59.360 --> 2:01:00.480
I'm surprised you picked up.

2:01:00.600 --> 2:01:02.040
I'm sorry, you have
the wrong number.

2:01:03.760 --> 2:01:05.280
She's in breach
of Senate Ethics rules.

2:01:06.360 --> 2:01:07.509
We can prove it.

2:01:08.200 --> 2:01:10.350
I placed George Dupont
under surveillance

2:01:11.560 --> 2:01:13.357
until he met with
a member of Congress

2:01:13.880 --> 2:01:15.950
who exhibited sufficient
moral bankruptcy

2:01:16.360 --> 2:01:18.715
to collude with such a plan.

2:01:18.840 --> 2:01:20.034
And go.

2:01:23.760 --> 2:01:25.557
That member was

2:01:25.680 --> 2:01:28.035
Senator
Ronald Michael Sperling.

2:01:30.240 --> 2:01:31.275
Order.

2:01:31.360 --> 2:01:33.351
This is not a platform
you can use

2:01:33.440 --> 2:01:35.160
to make malicious,
defamatory accusations...

2:01:35.240 --> 2:01:37.040
Input the following address
into your browser.

2:01:39.400 --> 2:01:42.870
193-dot-184

2:01:43.640 --> 2:01:48.873
dot-216-dot-449.

2:01:49.400 --> 2:01:52.756
Download a file
named "Earthquake."

2:01:54.560 --> 2:01:56.516
I can't
vote for it with one hand

2:01:56.600 --> 2:01:58.238
and choke it with the other...

2:02:07.440 --> 2:02:08.634
Get the car.

2:02:18.280 --> 2:02:20.748
In light of these allegations,
this hearing is adjourned.

2:02:29.440 --> 2:02:30.839
Back up, please.
Back up. Back up.

2:04:07.880 --> 2:04:09.279
I'm surprised you showed.

2:04:10.080 --> 2:04:11.160
I hear I'm not the only one

2:04:11.200 --> 2:04:12.520
whose visits
you've been refusing.

2:04:15.360 --> 2:04:16.873
You look good.

2:04:17.720 --> 2:04:19.711
Prison's not so bad
if you don't have a penis.

2:04:20.200 --> 2:04:22.509
We don't shank each other,
we form self-help groups.

2:04:24.040 --> 2:04:25.440
There's a black market
in lip gloss.

2:04:25.720 --> 2:04:26.720
Hmm.

2:04:27.960 --> 2:04:29.029
Why this time?

2:04:31.440 --> 2:04:32.873
They told me it was business.

2:04:33.440 --> 2:04:34.714
Yeah. Um...

2:04:35.560 --> 2:04:36.856
Now that the Sperling
and Dupont hearings

2:04:36.880 --> 2:04:37.949
are on the schedule,

2:04:38.040 --> 2:04:39.519
I'm petitioning
for an early release.

2:04:40.280 --> 2:04:41.554
You look good, too,
by the way.

2:04:42.040 --> 2:04:43.393
Thank you.

2:04:44.720 --> 2:04:48.235
I think we are looking
at four, maybe six months.

2:04:53.600 --> 2:04:55.113
You instigated
the whole thing.

2:04:58.280 --> 2:04:59.793
You weaponized yourself,

2:05:01.120 --> 2:05:02.678
brought the roof
of the US Capitol

2:05:02.760 --> 2:05:04.079
crashing down on your head.

2:05:05.000 --> 2:05:07.150
For what, a gun bill?

2:05:09.160 --> 2:05:11.469
- Worked, didn't it?
- Well, congrats.

2:05:12.440 --> 2:05:13.840
Criminals must now
endure the hassle

2:05:13.920 --> 2:05:15.672
of procuring their guns
on the black market.

2:05:17.520 --> 2:05:19.158
Was that really
worth your career?

2:05:21.680 --> 2:05:23.272
Career suicide is
not so bad when you

2:05:23.440 --> 2:05:26.000
consider the alternative
is suicide by career.

2:05:27.920 --> 2:05:29.114
My doctor would tell you

2:05:29.640 --> 2:05:31.437
I've served
my interest very well.

2:05:34.200 --> 2:05:35.200
Hmm.

2:05:38.160 --> 2:05:39.434
Thanks for coming, Daniel.

2:05:42.160 --> 2:05:43.388
I'm curious.

2:05:46.120 --> 2:05:47.553
Your little filing snafu?

2:05:49.440 --> 2:05:50.920
You filled out
that form deliberately.

2:05:51.000 --> 2:05:52.360
That was you,
throwing them a bone.

2:05:53.680 --> 2:05:55.961
Without it, they would have
nothing to incite the hearing.

2:05:57.160 --> 2:05:59.116
And you're under no obligation
to answer that.

2:06:05.360 --> 2:06:06.839
And you neglected
to mention this

2:06:06.960 --> 2:06:08.160
to any of your team because...

2:06:08.200 --> 2:06:09.315
Five years minimum.

2:06:16.240 --> 2:06:17.434
I'll be seeing you.
